1
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:21,907
(Based on the WEBTOON Series)

2
00:01:21,949 --> 00:01:23,250
( SingNsong)

3
00:01:35,862 --> 00:01:37,097
Hello, Author.

4
00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:39,232
My name is Kim Dok-ja.

5
00:01:41,568 --> 00:01:44,071
I read the last episode
which you uploaded today.

6
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:48,141
Your web novel, TWSA,

7
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:49,688
"Three Ways to
Survive the Apocalypse"

8
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:52,045
began publication

9
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:54,519
when I was in third
year of middle school.

10
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:59,185
Mammals include humans, bears...

11
00:01:59,252 --> 00:02:01,154
I still remember
the first sentence.

12
00:02:02,022 --> 00:02:03,123
"The subway car stopped,"

13
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,992
"in the middle of Dongho Bridge."

14
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:12,766
Planetary system 8612's
free service has ended.

15
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,768
To punish fallen humanity,

16
00:02:14,835 --> 00:02:16,836
the gods sent down
intolerable hardships,

17
00:02:16,903 --> 00:02:19,272
and as the world neared collapse,

18
00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:21,708
the hero Yu Jung-hyeok
and his companions

19
00:02:21,775 --> 00:02:23,210
overcame these trials.

20
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:28,682
At first, TWSA was quite popular.

21
00:02:28,749 --> 00:02:30,383
But as the story went on,

22
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:32,352
people called it too
extreme, or unrealistic.

23
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:33,987
Many stopped following.

24
00:02:42,095 --> 00:02:43,096
Hey, what's this?

25
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:44,631
Give it.

26
00:02:44,698 --> 00:02:45,978
- Let me see.
- Give me my phone!

27
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:47,767
You want to die?

28
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:49,336
Still, during my school days,

29
00:02:49,403 --> 00:02:51,171
this story was everything to me.

30
00:02:52,406 --> 00:02:53,807
With every update,

31
00:02:53,874 --> 00:02:56,643
I'd reread the last two
episodes to keep the flow.

32
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:59,546
On weekends, I re-read
the entire week's episodes.

33
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:03,083
And yes, when the views fell to 1,

34
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,951
I was the only reader.

35
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,421
Why read a novel for 10 years

36
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:10,023
when no one else was reading it?

37
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:12,625
Yu Jung-hyeok...

38
00:03:13,593 --> 00:03:14,593
I envied him.

39
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,165
(Geumho)

40
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:21,835
Yu and his companions

41
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:24,204
brought vicious
enemies to their knees,

42
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,706
and they never backed down

43
00:03:26,773 --> 00:03:28,442
while fighting monsters.

44
00:03:31,845 --> 00:03:32,913
Lee Hyeon-seong!

45
00:03:33,513 --> 00:03:36,483
But as his companions
fell one by one,

46
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:37,718
to survive,

47
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,254
Yu Jung-hyeok resolved
to become stronger.

48
00:03:44,991 --> 00:03:47,461
So he got stronger and stronger,

49
00:03:48,161 --> 00:03:51,064
but as I entered high school,
I stayed the same.

50
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:53,266
Now you two are going to fight.

51
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,602
The loser will be our doormat,

52
00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:57,337
but the winner gets freedom.

53
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:00,941
What, can't bear to
just save yourself?

54
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,544
Whatever, don't do it.

55
00:04:05,378 --> 00:04:08,882
But I told you for sure
what happens if you win!

56
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:13,620
"If only I could get stronger,"

57
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,155
"like Yu Jung-hyeok..."

58
00:04:16,957 --> 00:04:18,291
That's what I wished then.

59
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:25,398
I went to a mediocre college,

60
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:27,267
worked at some mediocre jobs,

61
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:29,002
then joined this company.

62
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:30,736
On a temp contract.

63
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:37,110
Today the novel ended,
and so did my contract.

64
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:40,046
Good work, Dok-ja.

65
00:04:41,214 --> 00:04:43,183
Call if you're in the area,
I'll treat you.

66
00:04:43,717 --> 00:04:44,885
Thanks.

67
00:04:52,526 --> 00:04:53,693
I appreciate your hard work

68
00:04:54,261 --> 00:04:56,797
running this story for so long.

69
00:04:58,198 --> 00:04:59,533
But still,

70
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:02,001
why'd you make Yu Jung-hyeok

71
00:05:02,068 --> 00:05:03,703
the only survivor at the end?

72
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:11,545
What's the meaning of
an ending with one survivor?

73
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:15,615
Yu Jung-hyeok once said,

74
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,084
"I can't help it"

75
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,220
"if others are
sacrificed so I can live."

76
00:05:21,454 --> 00:05:23,290
Is that the novel's theme?

77
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:26,493
I can't accept that.

78
00:05:28,028 --> 00:05:31,398
Sir, your novel is

79
00:05:32,232 --> 00:05:33,533
the worst.

80
00:05:37,571 --> 00:05:41,842
The train for Daehwa
is approaching.

81
00:05:55,789 --> 00:05:58,091
Listen to you sigh.

82
00:05:58,658 --> 00:05:59,993
Hi, Sang-ah.

83
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:02,495
Your last day, too?

84
00:06:03,964 --> 00:06:06,299
I knew they'd never
hire me full time.

85
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:08,668
No use fighting for
what can never be yours.

86
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:12,138
Just need to move on
and find a job that suits me.

87
00:06:14,908 --> 00:06:16,042
Thank you.

88
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,546
You've found a new job already?

89
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,182
I'm going to a part time job now.

90
00:06:22,249 --> 00:06:23,450
Need to survive this month.

91
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:27,187
You know how I designed
the characters' costumes?

92
00:06:27,254 --> 00:06:29,522
That work really suited me,

93
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:31,891
so I want to make real clothes.

94
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:34,594
Later, I'll launch
my own brand, open a shop.

95
00:06:34,661 --> 00:06:35,661
Nice, huh?

96
00:06:36,963 --> 00:06:38,565
You're so impressive, Sang-ah.

97
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:41,668
Sang-ah, fancy meeting you here!

98
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:43,570
Hello, Mr. Han.

99
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:45,271
I told you I'd buy dinner tonight.

100
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:46,873
I need to be somewhere.

101
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:51,144
I'm so sad that
our Sang-ah is quitting.

102
00:06:51,211 --> 00:06:53,513
If you'd given me a chance,

103
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,982
I'd have fought to get you hired.

104
00:06:56,049 --> 00:06:58,518
Not at all, my skills
weren't up to it.

105
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:02,055
Let's get off this train
and have dinner.

106
00:07:02,122 --> 00:07:03,690
I know a nice place in Apgujeong.

107
00:07:04,624 --> 00:07:05,491
I have a part-time job.

108
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:08,595
Hey, no excuses.
I'll pay for the hours you miss.

109
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,464
That's really okay.

110
00:07:12,065 --> 00:07:13,800
I'm going with someone.

111
00:07:15,302 --> 00:07:16,803
Your friend?

112
00:07:17,871 --> 00:07:19,706
Hello, Mr. Han.

113
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,641
I'm Kim Dok-ja from
Map Development.

114
00:07:25,378 --> 00:07:26,378
So you two have had

115
00:07:26,413 --> 00:07:27,947
something going on all this time?

116
00:07:28,014 --> 00:07:30,583
My, what a shame.

117
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:35,255
This stop is Apgujeong...
Apgujeong.

118
00:07:35,322 --> 00:07:36,923
The doors are on your right.

119
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:38,425
Enjoy your dinner.

120
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:42,128
Sure, Sang-ah.
I'll see you around.

121
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:48,067
What a jekr he is.

122
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,303
I couldn't even report him

123
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,410
for fear of getting fired.

124
00:07:52,205 --> 00:07:55,041
You did well.
Holding back is winning.

125
00:07:55,709 --> 00:07:58,478
It's not winning,
it's being an idiot.

126
00:07:58,545 --> 00:08:02,382
But even knowing that,
I can't say a word.

127
00:08:02,449 --> 00:08:03,616
Like an idiot.

128
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,085
You know how annoying that is?

129
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:13,860
(Dear Dok-ja, this is
the author of TWSA)

130
00:08:13,927 --> 00:08:16,796
(Thank you for reading my novel)

131
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:20,233
Just a minute.

132
00:08:24,804 --> 00:08:26,139
(You are really the author?)

133
00:08:26,206 --> 00:08:27,807
(This story was
able to reach its end)

134
00:08:27,874 --> 00:08:28,741
(thanks to you)

135
00:08:28,808 --> 00:08:30,210
The doors are closing.

136
00:08:31,945 --> 00:08:34,147
(No, thank you
for all your efforts)

137
00:08:34,214 --> 00:08:36,950
(I regret what I wrote
in my email, please...)

138
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:38,617
Your girlfriend?

139
00:08:39,486 --> 00:08:40,486
No.

140
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:44,557
(So I'll do a special epilogue)

141
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:46,292
(based on readers' submission)

142
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:48,061
(If you don't like the ending, )

143
00:08:48,128 --> 00:08:49,329
(try writing your own)

144
00:08:49,396 --> 00:08:51,631
(The service will
start soon, at 7 PM)

145
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:53,766
(Then show me)

146
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,935
(the ending)

147
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:57,904
(that you want)

148
00:08:57,971 --> 00:08:59,372
(tls123 has left the chat)

149
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:02,375
The ending I want?

150
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:07,313
- What does that mean?
- Next stop is Oksu.

151
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,415
Thank you.

152
00:09:10,617 --> 00:09:12,152
Readers' submissions at 7PM...

153
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:14,587
But I'm the only reader.

154
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:18,158
Does that mean I can
change the ending?

155
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:32,438
Are you okay?

156
00:09:32,505 --> 00:09:36,876
Planetary system 8612's
free service has ended.

157
00:09:37,377 --> 00:09:40,380
This is the start of paid content.

158
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,483
I repeat.

159
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:48,254
Planetary system 8612's
free service has ended.

160
00:09:48,321 --> 00:09:51,691
This is the start of paid content.

161
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,426
Can this really be...?

162
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:55,428
"An announcement
echoes through the air."

163
00:09:55,495 --> 00:09:58,598
"Planetary system 8612's
free service has ended."

164
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:01,534
"This is the start
of paid content."

165
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,637
(This fellow, who
I'll call a dokkaebi…)

166
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:06,473
What? A dokkaebi?

167
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:10,309
I'm so damned busy,
what is this crap?

168
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:12,112
Is someone playing a joke on us?

169
00:10:13,146 --> 00:10:16,315
This is just like
the start of the novel.

170
00:10:16,382 --> 00:10:17,383
Hello?

171
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:20,086
The Korean language
patch is working now.

172
00:10:20,153 --> 00:10:22,121
People, can you hear me?

173
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:23,222
Damn it!

174
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:25,024
What the hell is going on?

175
00:10:25,091 --> 00:10:27,527
Yes, I understand.

176
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:29,228
I know you're all busy,

177
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:31,798
but please listen up for a moment.

178
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:35,601
Get the train moving!
This is outrageous.

179
00:10:35,668 --> 00:10:37,403
Come now, quiet down.

180
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:41,174
You need to listen to
what I'm about to tell you.

181
00:10:41,241 --> 00:10:43,776
Cause I'm going to say
something super important...

182
00:10:43,843 --> 00:10:45,711
Shut up and let's get moving,

183
00:10:45,778 --> 00:10:47,346
before I rip you to shreds!

184
00:10:47,413 --> 00:10:48,347
I'm busy as hell

185
00:10:48,414 --> 00:10:50,550
and these jerks stopped the train?

186
00:10:50,617 --> 00:10:52,519
Bunch of stupid...

187
00:11:00,293 --> 00:11:02,962
I said quiet!

188
00:11:06,466 --> 00:11:10,770
Humans, I want
you to listen closely

189
00:11:10,837 --> 00:11:12,238
to every word I say.

190
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:15,541
High up there, those lofty beings

191
00:11:15,608 --> 00:11:18,277
far greater than any puny human

192
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:20,914
have at last come to a decision.

193
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:24,317
That humans,
the most vulgar, greedy,

194
00:11:24,384 --> 00:11:27,086
self-centered
race in the universe,

195
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:29,455
must all be punished!

196
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:31,924
Channel BI-7623 has opened.

197
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:33,226
Constellations are entering.

198
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:35,228
Welcome, dear Constellations!

199
00:11:35,295 --> 00:11:38,231
Some super interesting
things are about to happen,

200
00:11:38,298 --> 00:11:39,365
so come and watch!

201
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,602
From this moment on,

202
00:11:42,669 --> 00:11:46,339
all you humans will
be given a Scenario.

203
00:11:46,406 --> 00:11:48,374
How you solve that Scenario

204
00:11:48,441 --> 00:11:50,677
will determine your fate.

205
00:11:51,611 --> 00:11:54,314
The first Main Scenario
is starting.

206
00:11:57,617 --> 00:11:58,985
Since this is your first time,

207
00:11:59,052 --> 00:12:00,853
I'll explain it nicely.

208
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,456
Kill one or more living organisms

209
00:12:03,523 --> 00:12:05,024
in this subway car.

210
00:12:05,091 --> 00:12:06,459
Within 10 minutes.

211
00:12:06,526 --> 00:12:09,395
Succeed, and you
each get 300 coins.

212
00:12:09,462 --> 00:12:11,898
Fail, and you end up like him.

213
00:12:11,965 --> 00:12:13,166
Simple, huh?

214
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:17,136
Our dear Constellations
will be watching it all,

215
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:19,972
so pay no heed to laws or ethics.

216
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:22,709
Just show it to us.

217
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:26,079
The true nature of humanity.

218
00:12:49,302 --> 00:12:50,379
The phones don't work, right?

219
00:12:50,403 --> 00:12:51,604
No, they won't.

220
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:00,913
Are you alone?
Are your parents with you?

221
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:04,284
Are you going to kill me?

222
00:13:05,084 --> 00:13:06,919
Oh my god!

223
00:13:43,423 --> 00:13:44,423
Yu Jung-hyeok?

224
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:47,059
I need to get a grip.

225
00:13:47,126 --> 00:13:49,462
A novel that only I know
has become reality.

226
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:52,231
That means I know the future.

227
00:13:53,066 --> 00:13:55,368
Wait, then next...!

228
00:14:17,657 --> 00:14:19,725
First I have to
clear this Scenario.

229
00:14:19,792 --> 00:14:20,893
Let me think.

230
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,261
One or more living organisms,

231
00:14:22,328 --> 00:14:23,763
one or more living organisms...

232
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:25,190
(Kiil one or more
living organisms)

233
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:42,414
Sang-ah.

234
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:45,384
Hold onto this.

235
00:14:45,451 --> 00:14:46,619
I'll go save those people.

236
00:14:47,754 --> 00:14:49,422
Where are you going?
Are you crazy?

237
00:14:50,356 --> 00:14:51,924
You'll die if you go there.

238
00:14:52,925 --> 00:14:54,427
I know this.

239
00:14:54,494 --> 00:14:55,428
What?

240
00:14:55,495 --> 00:14:57,363
I know how to solve this.

241
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:07,373
Listen up a minute!

242
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:12,545
People, listen to me for a minute!

243
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,148
Hold on!

244
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,898
The first kill in this area
has taken place.

245
00:15:32,965 --> 00:15:35,368
The killer receives 300 coins.

246
00:15:36,903 --> 00:15:40,473
What? Hey, you.
How did you do that?

247
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,708
It says each person must kill

248
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:46,078
one or more living
organisms, right?

249
00:15:46,145 --> 00:15:49,382
It said living organism.

250
00:15:50,316 --> 00:15:52,118
It didn't say human.

251
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:55,321
Don't come closer!

252
00:15:56,022 --> 00:15:57,423
I'll kill them all.

253
00:15:57,490 --> 00:15:58,491
Wait! Wait!

254
00:15:58,558 --> 00:16:01,160
How many ants have you got?
Tell us that first.

255
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:05,565
Well...

256
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,367
Not enough for everyone.

257
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:10,136
Hey mister!

258
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:12,438
If there's not enough,
you should've said so.

259
00:16:12,505 --> 00:16:14,173
Why'd you kill one
before saying anything?

260
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,541
Then how will we decide?

261
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:16,942
Can we give it to the kids first?

262
00:16:17,009 --> 00:16:18,177
Hey lady!

263
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:20,946
Everyone's life is the same!

264
00:16:21,013 --> 00:16:22,481
Is only your kid's life important?

265
00:16:22,548 --> 00:16:23,416
Everyone calm down!

266
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:25,384
I wish we had enough
for everyone, but...

267
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:26,919
Then what'll you do?

268
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,155
There's no time, hurry!

269
00:16:29,222 --> 00:16:31,257
Hold on! Hold on!

270
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:34,393
I'm this guy's boss at work.

271
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:35,461
Just a minute.

272
00:16:37,763 --> 00:16:40,299
Look, why are you
making the call on this?

273
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:43,669
People with more life
experience should do that.

274
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:44,670
So give it.

275
00:16:44,737 --> 00:16:48,140
Mr. Han, that's true,
but people here...

276
00:16:48,207 --> 00:16:50,710
I'm saying, I'll do it.
Give it here.

277
00:16:58,117 --> 00:16:59,151
Don't push!

278
00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:01,687
Okay, okay!

279
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,961
Dammit, why won't you die?

280
00:17:15,167 --> 00:17:16,602
Are you insane?

281
00:17:16,669 --> 00:17:18,103
You want to die?

282
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:18,971
Here.

283
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,541
Both you and her can live, okay?

284
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:25,645
I've got my own bug. Here.

285
00:17:26,746 --> 00:17:28,581
A pathetic, useless bug.

286
00:17:28,648 --> 00:17:30,182
In the novel, Kim Nam-woon

287
00:17:30,249 --> 00:17:31,569
was part of Yu Jung-hyeok's team.

288
00:17:31,918 --> 00:17:33,652
Was he always like this?

289
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:34,587
Hey!

290
00:17:34,654 --> 00:17:35,755
Dammit.

291
00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:39,525
Then I can just kill you instead.

292
00:17:48,401 --> 00:17:51,137
Sure, if this is
just like the novel...

293
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,440
Spend 300 coins on strength.

294
00:17:55,508 --> 00:17:57,710
300 coins spent on strength.

295
00:17:57,777 --> 00:17:59,445
Strength is increased.

296
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:11,023
Son of a gun, now you're dead.

297
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:12,100
Kim Nam-woon has activated

298
00:18:12,124 --> 00:18:12,958
the Grimdark Awakening skill.

299
00:18:13,025 --> 00:18:14,527
In the novel, Nam-woon was first

300
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:16,295
to receive
the Constellation's Support.

301
00:18:16,362 --> 00:18:17,964
Why a guy like him?

302
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:36,148
Wow, I've got skills,
this is cool as hell!

303
00:18:37,316 --> 00:18:40,620
Want to save that old lady?
Then you die.

304
00:18:50,196 --> 00:18:52,398
Are ants' eggs
living organisms too?

305
00:18:55,301 --> 00:18:59,005
One organism killed.
300 coins paid as a reward.

306
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,146
Spend 3,000 coins on stamina.

307
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,419
Spend 3,000 coins on agility.

308
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:22,261
What the hell?

309
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:23,462
Why can't I hit you?

310
00:19:30,403 --> 00:19:31,737
Mister.

311
00:19:32,471 --> 00:19:35,140
Okay, I won't hurt the old lady.

312
00:19:35,207 --> 00:19:36,876
- Give me an ant.
- I changed my mind.

313
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,812
We don't need you in this story.

314
00:19:39,879 --> 00:19:41,547
What the hell are you saying?

315
00:19:44,417 --> 00:19:46,318
Hey, get out of the way!

316
00:19:48,254 --> 00:19:51,257
Out of the way!

317
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:56,529
Get away from her!

318
00:20:05,604 --> 00:20:07,006
Time is up.

319
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:09,041
The Scenario has ended.

320
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:25,391
Granny.

321
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:27,393
Please wake up, okay?

322
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:28,494
Granny.

323
00:20:37,636 --> 00:20:38,971
Dok-ja...

324
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:42,842
Are you okay?

325
00:20:57,022 --> 00:20:58,457
Ta-dah!

326
00:20:58,524 --> 00:21:00,793
Congrats to the 17 humans

327
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:03,863
who cleared the first Scenario.

328
00:21:04,530 --> 00:21:07,066
You were originally
supposed to kill each other,

329
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:10,536
but well, using the ants
isn't against the rules.

330
00:21:11,203 --> 00:21:13,072
The Constellations said this car

331
00:21:13,139 --> 00:21:14,807
was more fun than the others,

332
00:21:14,874 --> 00:21:16,542
so let's move on for now.

333
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:17,543
Now it's time

334
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:20,379
for Supporting
Constellations to determine

335
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:22,948
who will receive
the Constellation's Support.

336
00:21:23,616 --> 00:21:26,351
The Constellations'
Support is a tremendous gift!

337
00:21:26,418 --> 00:21:27,419
If you choose well,

338
00:21:27,486 --> 00:21:30,656
it'll be a big help in
clearing future Scenarios

339
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:35,461
Thanks to your actions,

340
00:21:35,528 --> 00:21:36,638
the following Constellations

341
00:21:36,662 --> 00:21:37,839
wish to give you their Support.

342
00:21:37,863 --> 00:21:40,999
What's this mean?
Support? Constellations?

343
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:44,136
The Constellations watch
over all the Scenarios

344
00:21:44,203 --> 00:21:46,639
from out in space.

345
00:21:47,506 --> 00:21:48,540
They enjoy laughing

346
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:51,210
at the struggles of
humans trying to survive.

347
00:21:52,444 --> 00:21:53,955
If you're chosen to
receive their Support,

348
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:55,548
it can be helpful.

349
00:21:56,482 --> 00:21:59,752
But someday,
that debt must be paid back.

350
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:00,819
(None of the Above)

351
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:23,475
Quick!

352
00:22:23,542 --> 00:22:24,643
Come to this side!

353
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:25,711
Quick!

354
00:22:43,262 --> 00:22:44,262
Lee Hyeon-seong!

355
00:22:44,797 --> 00:22:47,566
Another character who
fought with Yu Jung-hyeok.

356
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:53,338
Listen, don't rely on strength.

357
00:22:53,405 --> 00:22:54,273
Use your skill.

358
00:22:54,340 --> 00:22:55,073
My skill?

359
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:56,308
How do I do that?

360
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,010
At the bottom
right of your vision,

361
00:22:58,077 --> 00:22:59,144
there's a skill window.

362
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,646
If you just think
about your skill,

363
00:23:00,713 --> 00:23:01,747
it should work.

364
00:23:16,629 --> 00:23:17,963
Lee Hyeon-seong has activated

365
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,399
Great Mountain Push, Level 1.

366
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:24,737
Out of the way!

367
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:40,252
As soon as you get out,
run across the bridge.

368
00:23:40,319 --> 00:23:41,487
Fast as you can!

369
00:23:42,288 --> 00:23:43,088
I'm Lee Hyeon-seong.

370
00:23:43,155 --> 00:23:44,256
I'm Kim Dok-ja.

371
00:23:44,323 --> 00:23:45,323
Go on out.

372
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:59,305
Damn.

373
00:24:04,009 --> 00:24:05,210
What are you doing?

374
00:24:06,111 --> 00:24:07,146
Hurry, you need to go.

375
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:20,291
We need to go, come on.

376
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:25,831
Don't cry. Time's running out.

377
00:24:26,398 --> 00:24:27,633
What's your name?

378
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:28,867
Lee Gil-yeong.

379
00:24:29,535 --> 00:24:31,770
Gil-yeong, can you run fast?

380
00:24:31,837 --> 00:24:37,276
But my ant farm got
destroyed because of you.

381
00:24:37,343 --> 00:24:40,212
Really? I'm sorry.

382
00:24:40,713 --> 00:24:44,917
- But we really...
- No, apologizing isn't enough.

383
00:24:45,818 --> 00:24:47,786
You should take responsibility.

384
00:25:19,952 --> 00:25:22,387
A Sub Scenario has arrived.

385
00:25:22,454 --> 00:25:24,022
Cross the severed bridge.

386
00:25:24,089 --> 00:25:26,725
Why call it a severed
bridge when it's not?

387
00:25:26,792 --> 00:25:28,027
Cause it will be!

388
00:25:50,282 --> 00:25:53,652
This is so thrilling,
don't just stand there!

389
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:55,587
I'll raise the difficulty level.

390
00:26:21,613 --> 00:26:23,081
Dok-ja!

391
00:26:23,148 --> 00:26:24,516
I just thought of that.

392
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:26,318
It was only a thought,

393
00:26:26,385 --> 00:26:27,586
then the bridge's been...

394
00:26:27,653 --> 00:26:29,488
I'll go first, Sang-ah!

395
00:26:30,489 --> 00:26:31,489
Hyeon-seong!

396
00:26:37,029 --> 00:26:38,230
Sang-ah!

397
00:26:39,731 --> 00:26:40,811
You chose a sponsor, right?

398
00:26:40,866 --> 00:26:42,968
Your sponsor is helping you.

399
00:26:43,035 --> 00:26:44,336
Let's hurry!

400
00:26:46,338 --> 00:26:48,306
Soon, poisonous gas
will start to spread.

401
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:50,142
We need to get
underground quickly.

402
00:26:51,043 --> 00:26:52,444
And be sure to collect coins!

403
00:26:52,511 --> 00:26:53,645
That's most important.

404
00:26:53,712 --> 00:26:55,414
How do you know all this?

405
00:26:56,081 --> 00:26:57,749
First, let's get to
the subway station.

406
00:26:58,250 --> 00:27:00,385
Geumho Station is the closest.

407
00:27:00,452 --> 00:27:02,754
If we take the subway
line Yu took, it'll be safe.

408
00:27:03,489 --> 00:27:04,590
Wait.

409
00:27:05,357 --> 00:27:06,492
But at Chungmuro Station...

410
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,395
Early in the novel,

411
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:11,573
Yu died at Chungmuro Station

412
00:27:11,597 --> 00:27:12,597
fighting the Fire Dragon.

413
00:27:15,734 --> 00:27:17,436
Yu used his Regression Skill

414
00:27:17,503 --> 00:27:19,204
to go back to
the story's beginning,

415
00:27:20,239 --> 00:27:22,341
but in a world without a hero,

416
00:27:23,742 --> 00:27:24,742
everyone disappears.

417
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:32,117
The hero must not die.

418
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:35,988
But with the tactics I know,

419
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,524
one can't defeat
the Fire Dragon alone.

420
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:53,572
This is so tedious.

421
00:28:13,091 --> 00:28:16,795
What if I tell Yu Jung-hyeok
those tactics?

422
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:19,064
And if we fight together?

423
00:28:20,399 --> 00:28:22,401
Dok-ja, hurry!

424
00:28:23,235 --> 00:28:24,803
Wait, I'll come in a second!

425
00:28:27,139 --> 00:28:28,273
Hey, Yu Jung-hyeok!

426
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:47,960
What are you?

427
00:28:48,627 --> 00:28:50,996
Huh? Well...

428
00:28:51,797 --> 00:28:53,865
Kim Nam-woon
shouldn't die this soon.

429
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:55,700
Did you do that?

430
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:59,271
No, it wasn't me...

431
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:00,872
Yu Jung-hyeok has activated

432
00:29:00,939 --> 00:29:02,507
the Lie Detection skill.

433
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:08,446
What, you already
know how to use coins?

434
00:29:08,513 --> 00:29:11,416
It's not that...

435
00:29:11,483 --> 00:29:12,551
Mr. Dok-ja!

436
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:14,786
Are you okay?

437
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,822
I'm fine! Stay there!

438
00:29:17,656 --> 00:29:19,558
I'm really fine! Don't come!

439
00:29:19,625 --> 00:29:21,793
And you know Lee Hyeon-seong?

440
00:29:24,796 --> 00:29:27,399
- I met him today...
- I'll ask again.

441
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:30,068
What are you?

442
00:29:30,669 --> 00:29:34,306
If I say I read this in a novel,

443
00:29:34,373 --> 00:29:35,941
he'll never believe me, right?

444
00:29:38,877 --> 00:29:40,478
I'm Kim Dok-ja.

445
00:29:40,545 --> 00:29:42,981
In a few days you'll die fighting

446
00:29:43,048 --> 00:29:44,488
the Fire Dragon in
Chungmuro Station.

447
00:29:45,284 --> 00:29:46,051
Even if you Regress,

448
00:29:46,118 --> 00:29:47,918
it'll take a long time
to clear this Scenario.

449
00:29:48,420 --> 00:29:49,754
But if we go together,

450
00:29:49,821 --> 00:29:51,690
you can defeat the Fire Dragon.

451
00:29:53,025 --> 00:29:54,793
I know the tactics.

452
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:56,294
Yu Jung-hyeok has activated

453
00:29:56,361 --> 00:29:57,896
the Lie Detection skill.

454
00:30:03,235 --> 00:30:04,770
How do you know those tactics?

455
00:30:07,572 --> 00:30:10,542
My personal skill is Prophecy.

456
00:30:11,343 --> 00:30:12,711
So if you take me with you,

457
00:30:12,778 --> 00:30:15,180
you'll have no problem
with Scenarios.

458
00:30:15,247 --> 00:30:16,181
Let's cross the bridge.

459
00:30:16,248 --> 00:30:18,283
You'll go via
Geumho Station, right?

460
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:19,985
- Hey, Kim Dok-ja.
- Yes?

461
00:30:23,388 --> 00:30:25,056
Why are you doing this?

462
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:27,425
Tell me the tactics.

463
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:29,695
We can just go together
and clear the Scenario!

464
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:32,464
I can't stand taking
along other people.

465
00:30:32,531 --> 00:30:35,166
If I tell you, you'll drop me.

466
00:30:35,233 --> 00:30:37,202
I'll drop you anyway.

467
00:30:37,269 --> 00:30:39,771
Wait a minute, wait!

468
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:42,708
Mr. Yu, I have
a terrible fear of heights!

469
00:30:45,544 --> 00:30:47,479
This isn't right!

470
00:30:47,546 --> 00:30:49,114
First, let go... no, don't let go!

471
00:30:51,983 --> 00:30:52,983
Your last chance.

472
00:30:53,985 --> 00:30:55,620
Why'd this happen to the world?

473
00:30:57,823 --> 00:31:02,060
Why are humans being punished?

474
00:31:03,762 --> 00:31:06,398
How would I know that?

475
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:12,571
Survive and come to Chungmuro.
Then you'll know.

476
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:17,342
I'll let you know then
if I'll fight with you.

477
00:31:22,914 --> 00:31:26,451
Yu Jung-hyeok, you jerk!

478
00:31:27,986 --> 00:31:28,986
In a few days,

479
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:31,490
Yu will die fighting
the Fire Dragon.

480
00:31:32,357 --> 00:31:36,795
But for me to live,
the hero must not die.

481
00:31:39,498 --> 00:31:41,099
But before that,

482
00:31:43,368 --> 00:31:45,270
I'm going to die.

483
00:32:09,461 --> 00:32:11,830
A Hidden Scenario has arrived.

484
00:32:13,698 --> 00:32:16,868
Kill the ichthyosaur
and escape its stomach.

485
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:23,608
(Hidden Scenario:
Commander Slayer)

486
00:32:23,675 --> 00:32:25,410
Kill it to escape?

487
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:30,048
But I've got no items.

488
00:32:30,115 --> 00:32:31,750
Huh?

489
00:32:31,817 --> 00:32:32,984
He's alive? He's alive!

490
00:32:33,718 --> 00:32:35,720
Constellations, as you see,

491
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:38,790
a human has entered
the ichthyosaur's belly.

492
00:32:39,458 --> 00:32:42,127
Sure, if I get on
the dokkaebi's good side

493
00:32:42,194 --> 00:32:44,463
it can help me get
coins or an item.

494
00:32:46,198 --> 00:32:48,032
And the thing a dokkaebi
likes most of all...

495
00:32:48,099 --> 00:32:50,101
Am I right, Constellations?

496
00:32:50,168 --> 00:32:52,904
Hey, get over here.

497
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:56,307
The human's talking to me!
I'll go closer.

498
00:32:56,374 --> 00:32:57,843
You lowly human.

499
00:32:58,376 --> 00:32:59,811
You were quite a sight,

500
00:32:59,878 --> 00:33:01,780
playing God with that ant farm.

501
00:33:01,847 --> 00:33:04,082
And you were a real terror.

502
00:33:04,149 --> 00:33:05,869
Shooting people down
with your little laser.

503
00:33:06,618 --> 00:33:08,353
Speak with some respect.

504
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:12,524
If you don't like it,
just shoot me.

505
00:33:14,926 --> 00:33:17,128
How dare a foolish
human talk this way

506
00:33:17,195 --> 00:33:18,463
to a great dokkaebi.

507
00:33:18,530 --> 00:33:20,131
Hey, Bihyeong.

508
00:33:20,866 --> 00:33:22,434
You're doing a Star Stream, right?

509
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:26,304
What? You know my name?

510
00:33:26,371 --> 00:33:28,540
And how do you know
about Star Streams?

511
00:33:28,607 --> 00:33:30,275
Your channel must
be exploding now.

512
00:33:30,942 --> 00:33:32,911
Who else is as
entertaining as me so far?

513
00:33:33,912 --> 00:33:36,014
The Constellations
must be so curious

514
00:33:36,081 --> 00:33:37,616
what I'll do next.

515
00:33:38,917 --> 00:33:41,419
If you kill me now, can
you handle the blowback?

516
00:33:42,087 --> 00:33:45,490
But how do you know all this?

517
00:33:46,124 --> 00:33:48,093
Close your channel
for a sec, and let's talk.

518
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:52,597
Constellations, let's break

519
00:33:52,664 --> 00:33:54,566
for a quick advertisement!

520
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:01,372
Now talk.

521
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:04,676
How can an ordinary human
know about Star Streams?

522
00:34:04,743 --> 00:34:06,878
Ow, that hurts.

523
00:34:07,612 --> 00:34:09,380
That's not what matters here.

524
00:34:09,447 --> 00:34:10,982
What? You told me to close it!

525
00:34:12,117 --> 00:34:15,353
Bihyeong, you need to be clever.

526
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:16,921
How long will you keep panhandling

527
00:34:16,988 --> 00:34:18,290
as a lowly 9th grade dokkaebi?

528
00:34:19,591 --> 00:34:20,859
What are you saying?

529
00:34:20,926 --> 00:34:22,627
What does a dokkaebi do, anyway?

530
00:34:23,328 --> 00:34:25,296
Let Constellations
into your channel,

531
00:34:25,363 --> 00:34:28,567
and show them
stories about humans.

532
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:30,301
Get a lot of donations,

533
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:31,728
and you'll be
a 1st grade dokkaebi.

534
00:34:32,504 --> 00:34:34,706
But I can guarantee my story

535
00:34:34,773 --> 00:34:36,841
will be incredibly fun.

536
00:34:39,611 --> 00:34:41,212
Sign an exclusive
contract with me,

537
00:34:42,547 --> 00:34:44,115
and you'll be dokkaebi king.

538
00:34:44,716 --> 00:34:45,984
Wow.

539
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:51,089
You should know your place.

540
00:34:51,156 --> 00:34:52,891
Why sign a contract with someone

541
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:53,958
who's about to die?

542
00:34:54,326 --> 00:34:55,503
Why do you think
Constellations watch

543
00:34:55,527 --> 00:34:56,794
the Star Streams?

544
00:34:56,861 --> 00:34:58,263
Cause it's fun

545
00:34:58,330 --> 00:35:00,465
watching humans
struggle to survive.

546
00:35:00,532 --> 00:35:02,300
That's why they donate too.

547
00:35:03,802 --> 00:35:07,639
Right!
Then suppose we sign a contract.

548
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:10,542
In the subway I used
ants to clear the Scenario,

549
00:35:10,609 --> 00:35:12,710
and I fought Kim
Nam-woon using my skills.

550
00:35:12,777 --> 00:35:15,580
I was eaten by an ichthyosaur,
but if I escape,

551
00:35:15,647 --> 00:35:16,891
then keep clearing every Scenario

552
00:35:16,915 --> 00:35:17,916
after getting out...

553
00:35:17,983 --> 00:35:19,884
How many donations do you think

554
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:21,252
our channel will get?

555
00:35:21,820 --> 00:35:23,955
How can I believe
that you'll do all that?

556
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:27,125
Go see how many
donations you have now.

557
00:35:33,531 --> 00:35:34,432
Look at all this!

558
00:35:34,499 --> 00:35:38,169
How many zeros?
I can't believe this.

559
00:35:39,738 --> 00:35:41,773
Okay, let's sign a contract!

560
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,808
We split the profits 50:50, okay?

561
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:01,126
- Oh, it's started!
- Damn.

562
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:04,395
Constellations,
the ichthyosaur's stomach acid

563
00:36:04,462 --> 00:36:05,463
has started to flow.

564
00:36:05,530 --> 00:36:06,831
How will he escape this?

565
00:36:06,898 --> 00:36:09,033
Bihyeong, open the Dokkaebi Shop.

566
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:11,403
Huh? The Dokkaebi Shop?

567
00:36:12,003 --> 00:36:14,372
How do you know all this?

568
00:36:15,073 --> 00:36:20,712
(Dokkaebi Shop)

569
00:36:25,717 --> 00:36:27,585
He purchased an item!

570
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:29,654
Let's see what he'll do with it.

571
00:36:38,963 --> 00:36:40,264
Yu Jung-hyeok was trapped

572
00:36:40,331 --> 00:36:42,200
in an ichthyosaur's
stomach once, too.

573
00:36:43,835 --> 00:36:45,003
If you block all

574
00:36:45,070 --> 00:36:47,772
its stomach acid ducts
with thorns, it'll die.

575
00:36:48,873 --> 00:36:50,442
But the problem is,

576
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:53,545
there are so many of them...

577
00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:06,958
In a few days you'll die fighting

578
00:37:07,025 --> 00:37:08,626
the Fire Dragon in
Chungmuro Station.

579
00:37:08,693 --> 00:37:10,261
Even if you Regress,

580
00:37:10,328 --> 00:37:12,073
it'll take a long time
to clear this Scenario.

581
00:37:12,097 --> 00:37:13,164
But if we go together,

582
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:15,300
you can defeat the Fire Dragon.

583
00:37:34,853 --> 00:37:37,288
This Scenario is
a battle of endurance.

584
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:41,826
The last one!

585
00:37:55,673 --> 00:37:58,209
You've cleared
the Hidden Scenario.

586
00:37:58,276 --> 00:38:01,279
9,000 coins paid as a reward.

587
00:38:03,648 --> 00:38:05,249
What is this?

588
00:38:05,316 --> 00:38:08,486
Dok-ja, you defeated
an ichthyosaur!

589
00:38:08,553 --> 00:38:10,255
- Amazing!
- Out of the way!

590
00:38:29,607 --> 00:38:31,342
What?
That's the Ichthyosaur's Nucleus!

591
00:38:31,409 --> 00:38:33,611
How'd you know where it was?

592
00:38:34,179 --> 00:38:35,847
Put this on
the Dokkaebi Shop auction.

593
00:38:36,447 --> 00:38:39,284
Not to sell. I want a 1:1 trade.

594
00:38:39,984 --> 00:38:41,653
And I'll only trade
it for Ether of Faith.

595
00:38:42,387 --> 00:38:43,521
Put up a notification window

596
00:38:43,588 --> 00:38:44,722
when there's an offer.

597
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:47,725
Dok-ja, you're
starting to scare me.

598
00:38:47,792 --> 00:38:49,961
Killing the ichthyosaur
is one thing,

599
00:38:50,028 --> 00:38:52,830
but to know how
to find its nucleus,

600
00:38:52,897 --> 00:38:55,099
and wanting to trade
for Ether of Faith!

601
00:38:55,166 --> 00:38:58,603
Ether of Faith is so rare!

602
00:38:58,670 --> 00:39:01,239
I doubt anyone in the
early Scenarios will have it.

603
00:39:01,306 --> 00:39:04,542
Let's try to find it
as soon as we can.

604
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:07,345
And when I call you,
come right away.

605
00:39:07,412 --> 00:39:10,048
Open your Dokkaebi Shop
for me sometimes, okay?

606
00:39:10,582 --> 00:39:12,416
I'll do my best, Dok-ja!

607
00:39:12,483 --> 00:39:13,885
And it's nothing big,

608
00:39:13,952 --> 00:39:16,487
but here's a gift to
celebrate our contract.

609
00:39:16,554 --> 00:39:18,189
You'll need it when you go out.

610
00:39:19,858 --> 00:39:21,726
Oh, a Starter Pack?

611
00:39:21,793 --> 00:39:23,261
(Starter Pack for Novice)

612
00:39:23,328 --> 00:39:24,362
Nice.

613
00:39:46,251 --> 00:39:48,486
The Constellation
Hunter of the Dark Moon

614
00:39:48,553 --> 00:39:49,754
admires your endurance,

615
00:39:49,821 --> 00:39:51,322
and wishes to sponsor...

616
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:53,191
The Constellation
Bringer of Dark Light

617
00:39:53,258 --> 00:39:54,725
wishes to be your sponsor

618
00:39:54,792 --> 00:39:55,693
and join you on your journey.

619
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:59,964
Constellations, you're
enjoying this, huh?

620
00:40:11,576 --> 00:40:13,144
Hey Bihyeong!

621
00:40:13,211 --> 00:40:14,111
Turn off all notifications

622
00:40:14,178 --> 00:40:15,346
related to Constellations.

623
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:16,547
Yes, sir.

624
00:40:16,614 --> 00:40:18,149
But where'll you go now?

625
00:40:18,216 --> 00:40:21,185
Geumho Station.
Need to meet someone.

626
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:23,588
You mean that tall fellow?

627
00:40:23,655 --> 00:40:25,623
Don't do that.
He's got tons of items

628
00:40:25,690 --> 00:40:27,425
and his level is off the charts.

629
00:40:27,492 --> 00:40:29,026
We just signed a contract,

630
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:30,762
what'll I do if you die?

631
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:32,664
I'm hungry.

632
00:40:55,787 --> 00:40:58,289
Hey.

633
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:05,363
Hey! Can you hear me?

634
00:41:05,430 --> 00:41:06,798
Try to wake up.

635
00:41:08,533 --> 00:41:09,667
Can you stand up?

636
00:41:20,545 --> 00:41:21,746
Did you say exit 1?

637
00:41:26,050 --> 00:41:27,050
Wait!

638
00:41:30,955 --> 00:41:31,990
Wait a minute!

639
00:41:34,359 --> 00:41:35,359
Dammit!

640
00:42:00,785 --> 00:42:02,620
Hey, are you okay?

641
00:42:04,389 --> 00:42:05,690
- Over there.
- What's this?

642
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:07,358
It's really true!

643
00:42:08,159 --> 00:42:11,329
Jeong Hui-won, you're alive?

644
00:42:12,163 --> 00:42:15,666
- Jeong Hui-won?
- I thought you croaked.

645
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:17,035
I'll kill that lowlife.

646
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:18,970
Hey, mister!

647
00:42:19,504 --> 00:42:21,806
Why drag her back here

648
00:42:21,873 --> 00:42:26,244
after we've finished with her?

649
00:42:26,911 --> 00:42:28,513
Don't be a nuisance.

650
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:32,483
This chapter in the novel
was particularly boring.

651
00:42:33,618 --> 00:42:36,087
The characters were
such stereotypes.

652
00:42:36,154 --> 00:42:37,388
Bang Cheol-su?

653
00:42:38,122 --> 00:42:39,122
What's this?

654
00:42:39,490 --> 00:42:40,658
You know me?

655
00:42:41,859 --> 00:42:43,828
What are you waiting for? Come on.

656
00:42:44,462 --> 00:42:46,197
Spend 1,500 coins on strength.

657
00:42:46,264 --> 00:42:48,733
1,500 coins spent on strength.

658
00:42:53,871 --> 00:42:56,441
Holy crap, he's using skills?

659
00:42:57,909 --> 00:43:00,311
Hey, you should've told me!

660
00:43:00,378 --> 00:43:02,313
Bang Cheol-su is
blessed by his sponsor

661
00:43:02,380 --> 00:43:03,460
Monarch of the Small Fries.

662
00:43:04,215 --> 00:43:06,684
Why choose such a crappy sponsor?

663
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:09,186
Right, chest, right.

664
00:43:09,253 --> 00:43:10,755
This guy never changes.

665
00:43:17,829 --> 00:43:18,896
Boss!

666
00:43:18,963 --> 00:43:19,964
Kill that idiot!

667
00:43:20,565 --> 00:43:21,799
Now!

668
00:43:26,237 --> 00:43:27,572
Bang Cheol-su!

669
00:43:29,740 --> 00:43:31,809
What's going on here?

670
00:43:31,876 --> 00:43:33,544
Damn...

671
00:43:33,611 --> 00:43:35,046
Hey, let's go.

672
00:43:45,957 --> 00:43:49,360
Wait, who was this guy?

673
00:43:52,196 --> 00:43:53,431
Huh?

674
00:43:53,498 --> 00:43:54,966
Dok-ja!

675
00:44:04,775 --> 00:44:06,977
People say they've survived here

676
00:44:07,044 --> 00:44:09,046
thanks to that congressman.

677
00:44:09,981 --> 00:44:13,717
He persuades high-level
people to go out and hunt,

678
00:44:13,784 --> 00:44:15,753
then shares it with the residents.

679
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:18,122
It's done. You'll heal in no time.

680
00:44:21,125 --> 00:44:24,428
Gil-yeong!
I told you to stop that!

681
00:44:24,495 --> 00:44:26,097
Why? They're my friends.

682
00:44:26,164 --> 00:44:28,799
He's been acting weird
ever since that day.

683
00:44:28,866 --> 00:44:30,901
He says he can talk to bugs

684
00:44:30,968 --> 00:44:32,002
with his hands like that.

685
00:44:32,069 --> 00:44:34,071
I'm not weird. I like doing this.

686
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:38,442
But Mr. Dok-ja,

687
00:44:39,944 --> 00:44:43,414
why did that man on
the bridge drop you?

688
00:44:43,981 --> 00:44:45,183
What?

689
00:44:46,951 --> 00:44:48,519
Oh, him?

690
00:44:48,586 --> 00:44:49,987
I've known him since I was young.

691
00:44:50,488 --> 00:44:52,790
He's always been
hard to get along with.

692
00:44:53,958 --> 00:44:55,293
Didn't he cause a scene here too?

693
00:44:55,927 --> 00:44:57,995
No, he wasn't here.

694
00:45:00,231 --> 00:45:01,031
He hasn't been here?

695
00:45:01,098 --> 00:45:02,566
He crossed the bridge,

696
00:45:02,633 --> 00:45:03,873
and even when the gas came out,

697
00:45:03,935 --> 00:45:05,670
he just walked on
his own to Namsan.

698
00:45:06,737 --> 00:45:08,606
Yu Jung-hyeok didn't
come to Geumho Station?

699
00:45:09,941 --> 00:45:11,275
That can't be.

700
00:45:12,176 --> 00:45:13,911
Wait, so you haven't cleared

701
00:45:13,978 --> 00:45:15,880
the Geumho Station Scenario?

702
00:45:16,514 --> 00:45:17,691
Some people went into the tunnel

703
00:45:17,715 --> 00:45:19,150
trying to clear it,

704
00:45:19,717 --> 00:45:21,285
but no one came back.

705
00:45:22,753 --> 00:45:25,222
Damn, if we can't clear it,

706
00:45:25,289 --> 00:45:27,325
we can't pass the barrier
and get to Chungmuro.

707
00:45:27,925 --> 00:45:30,294
But why are things
different from the novel?

708
00:45:30,828 --> 00:45:33,397
Listen up, residents!

709
00:45:34,131 --> 00:45:36,667
The survival fee
payment is due in 3 hours.

710
00:45:37,401 --> 00:45:40,471
The Search Party
will leave in 5 minutes,

711
00:45:40,538 --> 00:45:41,539
so be ready.

712
00:45:42,039 --> 00:45:43,841
Let the elderly stay,

713
00:45:43,908 --> 00:45:46,777
and healthy men
who want to go out...

714
00:45:46,844 --> 00:45:48,179
The Geumho Station Scenario

715
00:45:48,246 --> 00:45:50,614
exacts a survival
fee on all residents

716
00:45:50,681 --> 00:45:52,783
until the monsters are defeated.

717
00:45:53,484 --> 00:45:54,919
100 coins per day.

718
00:45:55,653 --> 00:45:57,288
Residents desperate for coins

719
00:45:57,788 --> 00:45:59,156
went out on dangerous hunts,

720
00:46:00,658 --> 00:46:02,627
and those who couldn't pay

721
00:46:04,195 --> 00:46:07,064
died on the spot.

722
00:46:08,866 --> 00:46:09,867
Hey you!

723
00:46:11,702 --> 00:46:12,870
You, the newcomer.

724
00:46:16,674 --> 00:46:19,009
They say you grabbed
all the coins for yourself,

725
00:46:19,076 --> 00:46:20,077
is it true?

726
00:46:21,045 --> 00:46:21,879
What?

727
00:46:21,946 --> 00:46:22,713
You earned coins

728
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:25,082
by hunting monsters
in this district, right?

729
00:46:25,650 --> 00:46:27,518
Then share the coins.

730
00:46:27,585 --> 00:46:29,920
How can you just keep quiet?

731
00:46:29,987 --> 00:46:32,056
Give them to the Congressman

732
00:46:32,123 --> 00:46:33,290
so they can be shared.

733
00:46:33,357 --> 00:46:34,959
Think only you have it hard?

734
00:46:35,026 --> 00:46:36,360
Right!

735
00:46:37,595 --> 00:46:40,497
I think there's been
some misunderstanding.

736
00:46:40,564 --> 00:46:42,166
I've never gone out hunting.

737
00:46:42,233 --> 00:46:44,635
Don't lie to us!

738
00:46:44,702 --> 00:46:46,136
You fight so well

739
00:46:46,203 --> 00:46:49,206
because you earned
coins while hunting!

740
00:46:49,273 --> 00:46:51,108
No really, I've never hunted.

741
00:46:51,742 --> 00:46:54,979
And even if I did, wouldn't
the reward be mine?

742
00:46:55,046 --> 00:46:56,547
Listen to him!

743
00:46:56,614 --> 00:46:59,083
Here at Geumho Station,

744
00:46:59,150 --> 00:47:02,953
we've survived up to now
by pooling our strength!

745
00:47:06,457 --> 00:47:07,825
Oh, right.

746
00:47:08,526 --> 00:47:09,527
You must have.

747
00:47:10,194 --> 00:47:14,231
But who told you that
I have a lot of coins?

748
00:47:14,865 --> 00:47:16,367
Why does that matter?

749
00:47:16,967 --> 00:47:19,203
Go to the office and turn them in.

750
00:47:19,737 --> 00:47:20,838
We're desperate here.

751
00:47:20,905 --> 00:47:22,706
So just tell me.

752
00:47:22,773 --> 00:47:25,810
Then I'll give you
each 100 coins, okay?

753
00:47:26,944 --> 00:47:28,412
Who told you?

754
00:47:28,479 --> 00:47:29,580
Bang Cheol-su?

755
00:47:30,548 --> 00:47:32,450
I told them.

756
00:47:36,620 --> 00:47:37,721
With such abilities,

757
00:47:37,788 --> 00:47:40,024
I assumed you were rich in coins.

758
00:47:40,091 --> 00:47:43,127
But those with a lot
are least willing to share.

759
00:47:44,195 --> 00:47:47,965
I hoped you'd understand
our situation here.

760
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:51,302
With everyone so desperate,
we acted a bit rude.

761
00:47:52,236 --> 00:47:54,638
If you were offended, I apologize.

762
00:47:54,705 --> 00:47:57,274
No, I'm not offended.

763
00:47:59,176 --> 00:48:01,078
Mr. Kim, 20 people can't afford

764
00:48:01,145 --> 00:48:03,280
the survival fee today.

765
00:48:04,715 --> 00:48:06,050
I want to save our residents

766
00:48:06,117 --> 00:48:07,251
by any means possible.

767
00:48:08,552 --> 00:48:11,288
Please help us, I beg you.

768
00:48:13,924 --> 00:48:17,161
Wait, now I remember.

769
00:48:17,661 --> 00:48:19,263
I know who he is...

770
00:48:20,898 --> 00:48:22,233
You want my coins.

771
00:48:23,901 --> 00:48:25,669
That's not going to happen.

772
00:48:29,874 --> 00:48:32,643
You don't care
if our residents die?

773
00:48:32,710 --> 00:48:35,012
Even if they live today,
what about tomorrow?

774
00:48:35,579 --> 00:48:37,715
People are dying right now!

775
00:48:37,782 --> 00:48:39,283
How can you say that?

776
00:48:39,350 --> 00:48:41,118
That's enough.

777
00:48:43,053 --> 00:48:45,456
Stop this, okay?

778
00:48:47,591 --> 00:48:48,692
Stop!

779
00:48:51,195 --> 00:48:52,596
Will you?

780
00:48:54,365 --> 00:48:56,500
I thought you were
a good person, Mr. Kim.

781
00:48:59,069 --> 00:49:00,805
But I read you wrong.

782
00:49:04,742 --> 00:49:05,943
All right.

783
00:49:06,510 --> 00:49:07,678
I'll help.

784
00:49:10,781 --> 00:49:12,583
But even if I give you coins,

785
00:49:12,650 --> 00:49:14,151
you'll need more tomorrow.

786
00:49:14,885 --> 00:49:15,953
So instead...

787
00:49:17,588 --> 00:49:19,089
"Pass through the tunnel"

788
00:49:19,156 --> 00:49:21,792
"and neutralize all the monsters."

789
00:49:21,859 --> 00:49:24,995
I'll clear this Scenario today.

790
00:49:25,930 --> 00:49:26,930
Okay?

791
00:49:28,732 --> 00:49:30,234
Cheon In-ho of Geumho Station,

792
00:49:31,235 --> 00:49:33,737
who sold himself
to the Constellations,

793
00:49:35,339 --> 00:49:37,341
who gave up his
humanity to become

794
00:49:38,442 --> 00:49:39,877
a monster.

795
00:49:39,944 --> 00:49:42,112
Ant eggs instead of humans?

796
00:49:43,013 --> 00:49:45,382
That was allowed?

797
00:49:47,251 --> 00:49:49,486
If a man like you
was beaten by him,

798
00:49:49,553 --> 00:49:51,088
the rumors must be true.

799
00:49:52,423 --> 00:49:54,892
Kim Dok-ja has
the highest abilities

800
00:49:54,959 --> 00:49:57,127
and most coins in
Geumho Station now.

801
00:49:57,728 --> 00:50:00,531
If he's that strong,
can he clear the Scenario?

802
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:06,971
How many times must I tell you?

803
00:50:07,638 --> 00:50:08,539
As long as I'm here,

804
00:50:08,606 --> 00:50:10,574
no one will clear that Scenario.

805
00:50:11,141 --> 00:50:12,343
Ah, yes.

806
00:50:12,910 --> 00:50:14,111
You're right.

807
00:50:14,178 --> 00:50:15,679
Of course, you're right.

808
00:50:19,316 --> 00:50:22,286
It's human nature to bow
down before the strong.

809
00:50:22,786 --> 00:50:24,321
A weakling like him

810
00:50:24,388 --> 00:50:26,657
who suddenly gains great strength

811
00:50:26,724 --> 00:50:29,293
will run wild, thinking
he's a big shot.

812
00:50:31,328 --> 00:50:33,130
It's reckless gallantry.

813
00:50:34,565 --> 00:50:37,835
In this world,
guys like him die first.

814
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:42,239
Then if he dies,
we better collect his coins.

815
00:50:42,306 --> 00:50:44,641
How much do you think he has?

816
00:50:44,708 --> 00:50:47,511
I heard it's tens of
thousands of coins.

817
00:50:48,812 --> 00:50:50,114
Is that true, Mr. Han?

818
00:50:52,383 --> 00:50:54,318
Yes, it's true! Sorry.

819
00:50:55,119 --> 00:50:56,353
I saw it clearly.

820
00:50:58,222 --> 00:50:59,223
Help yourself.

821
00:51:04,428 --> 00:51:05,529
I'm not going.

822
00:51:05,596 --> 00:51:07,331
Why go? We'll die.

823
00:51:07,398 --> 00:51:09,166
We won't die. Come along.

824
00:51:09,233 --> 00:51:10,467
I'll go, mister!

825
00:51:10,534 --> 00:51:13,003
I want to fight monsters, too.

826
00:51:13,070 --> 00:51:16,173
Look at him saying
he'll fight monsters.

827
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:17,307
No way.

828
00:51:17,374 --> 00:51:19,977
Mr. Dok-ja, if you
have extra coins,

829
00:51:20,044 --> 00:51:21,845
why not just share them?

830
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:24,748
Exactly!
Why do we have to go this far?

831
00:51:24,815 --> 00:51:27,384
I mean you, not we.

832
00:51:28,552 --> 00:51:30,421
Even with coins,
people here will die.

833
00:51:31,322 --> 00:51:34,625
To stop the deaths,
we must target the cause.

834
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:37,427
Isn't that so, Hui-won?

835
00:51:39,863 --> 00:51:43,300
In the novel, Hui-won
rebels against Cheon In-ho,

836
00:51:43,367 --> 00:51:44,935
loses her friends

837
00:51:45,002 --> 00:51:46,670
and dies in the convenience store.

838
00:51:48,005 --> 00:51:52,242
Now, all she has left is rage.

839
00:51:52,309 --> 00:51:56,580
You say that congressman
is the culprit... how?

840
00:51:56,647 --> 00:51:58,582
When I found Hui-won,

841
00:51:58,649 --> 00:52:00,450
it wasn't monsters
that had attacked her.

842
00:52:00,517 --> 00:52:02,319
Bang Cheol-su's gang
is on his side too.

843
00:52:02,820 --> 00:52:04,021
They recruit a Search Party

844
00:52:04,088 --> 00:52:05,355
to go out looking for coins,

845
00:52:05,422 --> 00:52:07,691
and after hunting,
they quietly kill everyone.

846
00:52:07,758 --> 00:52:10,628
My friends died trying
to stop them with me.

847
00:52:11,261 --> 00:52:14,031
Why would they kill people?

848
00:52:14,832 --> 00:52:17,368
When you die,
your coins all fall out.

849
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:21,205
That jerk Cheon In-ho
is not human.

850
00:52:24,908 --> 00:52:26,377
It's too dark here.

851
00:52:26,910 --> 00:52:29,046
We can't even
walk, let alone fight.

852
00:52:31,782 --> 00:52:34,017
Gil-yeong, can you help?

853
00:52:34,084 --> 00:52:36,153
Me? Can I?

854
00:52:36,220 --> 00:52:37,321
What are you talking about?

855
00:52:39,657 --> 00:52:41,959
That thing you
thought of, show me.

856
00:52:44,695 --> 00:52:46,797
Hey Gil-yeong, don't you
dare call cockroaches!

857
00:53:11,755 --> 00:53:13,490
Wow, Lee Gil-yeong!

858
00:53:18,128 --> 00:53:20,431
They say monsters are coming.

859
00:53:27,071 --> 00:53:28,472
Make use of your sponsors.

860
00:53:29,573 --> 00:53:31,675
You know how to increase
your abilities with coins?

861
00:53:31,742 --> 00:53:34,044
Spend all your coins
on strength and agility.

862
00:53:34,111 --> 00:53:35,112
All my coins?

863
00:53:35,179 --> 00:53:37,014
Shouldn't I save some
for the survival fee?

864
00:53:40,417 --> 00:53:41,952
Maintain this formation.

865
00:53:42,619 --> 00:53:44,722
Don't fight on your own,
help each other.

866
00:53:45,222 --> 00:53:46,690
Gil-yeong, keep
the fireflies steady.

867
00:53:47,825 --> 00:53:49,126
I'm going to fight too!

868
00:53:50,194 --> 00:53:51,595
Stay behind me.

869
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:03,906
I'll go!

870
00:54:27,264 --> 00:54:29,800
If we follow that one...

871
00:54:36,373 --> 00:54:37,808
Mister, if we go this way,

872
00:54:37,875 --> 00:54:39,976
there'll be a really
strong monster, right?

873
00:54:40,043 --> 00:54:41,845
The fireflies told me.

874
00:54:41,912 --> 00:54:43,046
What?

875
00:54:43,113 --> 00:54:43,880
I don't know.

876
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:47,684
But you always
know a ton of stuff.

877
00:54:47,751 --> 00:54:49,486
You're like a god.

878
00:54:49,553 --> 00:54:51,321
Would I be doing
this if I were a god?

879
00:54:51,388 --> 00:54:53,757
If there's a god,
it's that author.

880
00:54:58,662 --> 00:54:59,763
Sang-ah!

881
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:01,131
Are you there?

882
00:55:01,198 --> 00:55:03,567
Dok-ja! I'm tied up here...

883
00:55:03,634 --> 00:55:05,169
What's that?

884
00:55:09,506 --> 00:55:12,176
You've entered
The Ground Rat's Shrine.

885
00:55:22,986 --> 00:55:24,154
I'll go first!

886
00:55:48,345 --> 00:55:50,647
Do I need an item to
defeat a demon species?

887
00:55:50,714 --> 00:55:51,949
Mr. Dok-ja! I'm coming!

888
00:55:52,749 --> 00:55:54,651
Hyeon-seong! It's no use!

889
00:56:08,565 --> 00:56:10,934
What the... Can he do that?

890
00:56:14,571 --> 00:56:16,106
The Warden of the Dark

891
00:56:16,173 --> 00:56:18,475
has activated an Illusory Prison.

892
00:56:18,542 --> 00:56:19,576
Illusory Prison?

893
00:56:22,412 --> 00:56:23,772
The Illusory Prison traps the body

894
00:56:23,814 --> 00:56:24,915
and wrecks the mind.

895
00:56:25,415 --> 00:56:26,750
If you're caught in it,

896
00:56:26,817 --> 00:56:28,952
you relive awful memories and die.

897
00:56:31,889 --> 00:56:33,690
Run, Hui-won!

898
00:56:54,878 --> 00:56:55,879
What was that?

899
00:56:55,946 --> 00:56:57,614
Just a second.

900
00:56:58,115 --> 00:57:00,317
Gil-yeong! No!

901
00:57:18,835 --> 00:57:20,203
Over there!

902
00:57:51,368 --> 00:57:53,537
Hui-won! Buy me some time!

903
00:57:55,272 --> 00:57:56,673
Hey Bihyeong, you watching?

904
00:57:56,740 --> 00:57:58,141
Yes, what do you need?

905
00:57:58,208 --> 00:58:00,510
Open the Dokkaebi Shop.
White Star Pure Energy.

906
00:58:00,577 --> 00:58:04,114
It's 50,000 coins,
you're 1,000 coins short!

907
00:58:33,944 --> 00:58:35,478
50,000 coins paid.

908
00:58:35,545 --> 00:58:37,614
You have bought
White Star Pure Energy.

909
00:58:42,919 --> 00:58:45,088
Your weapon can now deliver

910
00:58:45,155 --> 00:58:46,423
a One-time Critical Hit.

911
00:59:07,144 --> 00:59:08,211
Hyeon-seong!

912
00:59:43,747 --> 00:59:45,148
He's awake.

913
00:59:45,215 --> 00:59:46,316
Are you okay?

914
00:59:47,551 --> 00:59:50,487
Sorry. I must've fallen asleep.

915
00:59:52,823 --> 00:59:54,124
Just a minute.

916
00:59:56,993 --> 00:59:59,262
If you rest, you'll feel better.

917
01:00:00,597 --> 01:00:03,767
The Hyeon-seong in the novel
was wracked by guilt

918
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:06,069
for not saving someone,

919
01:00:06,136 --> 01:00:09,206
so he could not make
use of his abilities.

920
01:00:09,940 --> 01:00:13,944
The Lee Hyeon-seong
here is exactly the same.

921
01:00:16,046 --> 01:00:18,315
Nice work, everyone.

922
01:00:18,815 --> 01:00:21,851
I saw some treasure
chests back there.

923
01:00:21,918 --> 01:00:23,386
Let's each go open one.

924
01:00:27,290 --> 01:00:28,591
Two swords for Hui-won,

925
01:00:28,658 --> 01:00:30,160
an arm protector for Hyeon-seong.

926
01:00:31,795 --> 01:00:32,729
What about Gil-yeong?

927
01:00:32,796 --> 01:00:36,266
With this, I can hear
the insects' words better.

928
01:00:36,333 --> 01:00:37,567
Ta-dah!

929
01:00:38,235 --> 01:00:39,402
Nice, huh?

930
01:00:40,003 --> 01:00:42,072
It seems this'll make
me able to fight well, too.

931
01:00:42,672 --> 01:00:44,708
Then I'll open up mine.

932
01:01:06,329 --> 01:01:08,031
Huh? Yours is defective.

933
01:01:08,098 --> 01:01:10,967
Why does the one who
worked hardest get that?

934
01:01:12,636 --> 01:01:14,538
It'll have some use, I'm sure.

935
01:01:15,071 --> 01:01:16,406
Let's go.

936
01:01:16,473 --> 01:01:18,341
This is it. The Broken Faith.

937
01:01:19,242 --> 01:01:21,144
Now if I can just
find An Ether of Faith,

938
01:01:21,211 --> 01:01:22,679
the weapon will be complete.

939
01:01:24,147 --> 01:01:26,183
Huh, what's this?

940
01:01:26,783 --> 01:01:29,486
Mister, I found
this here, what is it?

941
01:01:31,988 --> 01:01:35,258
If you eat this, those
white hands will come out,

942
01:01:35,325 --> 01:01:36,660
and you'll have scary dreams.

943
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:39,796
Keep away from it, okay?

944
01:01:39,863 --> 01:01:40,997
All right.

945
01:01:43,800 --> 01:01:44,800
Dok-ja.

946
01:01:45,869 --> 01:01:47,404
How do you know all this?

947
01:01:48,572 --> 01:01:50,039
What?

948
01:01:50,106 --> 01:01:52,375
Putting stuff on the knife,

949
01:01:52,442 --> 01:01:54,110
and you seem to know this place.

950
01:01:55,011 --> 01:01:57,147
It's like you've already
lived in this world.

951
01:01:58,315 --> 01:01:59,149
It's true, right?

952
01:01:59,216 --> 01:02:00,884
It's not just me who thinks that.

953
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:03,153
What is up with you?

954
01:02:04,654 --> 01:02:06,156
About that...

955
01:02:07,457 --> 01:02:10,594
I have no sponsor
or special skills,

956
01:02:11,361 --> 01:02:16,232
but it seems I know
a bit about what will happen.

957
01:02:16,299 --> 01:02:17,901
A kind of prophecy.

958
01:02:17,968 --> 01:02:19,869
You really know what'll happen?

959
01:02:19,936 --> 01:02:24,507
Prophecy? Dok-ja, that's awesome!

960
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:26,776
Then do you know what
will happen to the world?

961
01:02:26,843 --> 01:02:28,511
Shouldn't you know that, too?

962
01:02:30,247 --> 01:02:34,317
The world can go
back to how it was.

963
01:02:34,918 --> 01:02:36,319
Really?

964
01:02:36,386 --> 01:02:39,556
When? When can I go home?

965
01:02:40,156 --> 01:02:42,458
That'll take some time.

966
01:02:42,525 --> 01:02:44,327
What do we have to do?

967
01:02:46,830 --> 01:02:50,300
We have to clear up
to the 99th Scenario.

968
01:02:50,367 --> 01:02:53,737
The 99th? Who can do that?

969
01:02:54,571 --> 01:02:55,939
There's one person who can.

970
01:02:56,873 --> 01:02:58,708
A hero who can clear all Scenarios

971
01:02:59,376 --> 01:03:00,543
and save the world.

972
01:03:01,845 --> 01:03:04,648
It's not... you?

973
01:03:08,618 --> 01:03:11,054
The two of you saw him,
back on Dongho Bridge.

974
01:03:12,389 --> 01:03:13,857
Yu Jung-hyeok.

975
01:03:29,506 --> 01:03:31,040
That man?

976
01:03:31,107 --> 01:03:32,542
He's so good-looking.

977
01:03:32,609 --> 01:03:33,877
The problem is,

978
01:03:35,111 --> 01:03:38,081
tomorrow he will die
fighting a monster.

979
01:03:38,882 --> 01:03:40,383
What happens if he dies?

980
01:03:41,451 --> 01:03:43,053
Then this world is finished.

981
01:03:43,920 --> 01:03:46,156
It can never go
back to how it was.

982
01:03:47,624 --> 01:03:49,526
He'll be at Chungmuro Station now.

983
01:03:50,527 --> 01:03:52,061
Once we clear this Scenario,

984
01:03:52,128 --> 01:03:53,296
the barrier will be lifted,

985
01:03:53,997 --> 01:03:55,732
then I'll go there.

986
01:03:55,799 --> 01:03:57,267
I'll try to stop it somehow.

987
01:03:57,334 --> 01:03:58,368
Wait.

988
01:03:59,069 --> 01:04:01,471
Didn't we just
clear this Scenario?

989
01:04:02,005 --> 01:04:03,406
There's one monster left.

990
01:04:06,843 --> 01:04:09,212
10 minutes until
the survival fee payment.

991
01:04:09,279 --> 01:04:11,714
Prepare your payment.

992
01:04:11,781 --> 01:04:13,025
I heard people in the Search Party

993
01:04:13,049 --> 01:04:15,318
are being killed for coins?

994
01:04:15,385 --> 01:04:16,686
My husband isn't back yet!

995
01:04:16,753 --> 01:04:18,588
Goodness, you're annoying!

996
01:04:18,655 --> 01:04:21,357
I killed him. So what?

997
01:04:21,424 --> 01:04:23,192
- You didn't!
- What are you going to do?

998
01:04:23,259 --> 01:04:24,861
Annoying idiot.

999
01:04:29,032 --> 01:04:30,633
I told you I'd kill you.

1000
01:04:33,136 --> 01:04:34,237
Sweet dreams.

1001
01:04:41,378 --> 01:04:42,746
Ms. Jeong Hui-won!

1002
01:04:44,514 --> 01:04:46,949
If you went to clear the Scenario,

1003
01:04:47,016 --> 01:04:48,518
you should do it or die trying.

1004
01:04:48,585 --> 01:04:51,154
What's all this?

1005
01:04:52,689 --> 01:04:54,124
I'm here to clear it.

1006
01:04:54,624 --> 01:04:56,826
There's one monster left here.

1007
01:05:00,296 --> 01:05:01,398
Don't just stand there.

1008
01:05:02,799 --> 01:05:04,567
Kill them and take their coins.

1009
01:05:14,277 --> 01:05:16,979
In the novel, Jeong Hui-won
wasn't that famous,

1010
01:05:17,046 --> 01:05:19,082
and wasn't used much in the story.

1011
01:05:19,582 --> 01:05:21,884
Perhaps that's why
I cheered for her

1012
01:05:21,951 --> 01:05:23,853
more than anyone.

1013
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:27,924
Hui-won, in this story,
you are the hero.

1014
01:05:28,691 --> 01:05:31,260
The Constellation
Demonic Judge of Fire

1015
01:05:31,327 --> 01:05:33,496
approves use of this skill.

1016
01:05:35,899 --> 01:05:38,835
Time of Judgment
has been activated.

1017
01:06:47,103 --> 01:06:48,103
Hey, wait!

1018
01:06:48,571 --> 01:06:49,639
Miss!

1019
01:06:53,910 --> 01:06:56,246
You're not really going
to kill him, are you?

1020
01:06:56,880 --> 01:06:58,548
You may not know this,

1021
01:06:59,382 --> 01:07:01,083
but we don't clear this Scenario.

1022
01:07:01,150 --> 01:07:03,886
If we clear it, the next
one gets even harder.

1023
01:07:03,953 --> 01:07:07,123
At a nearby station they
opened the next Scenario

1024
01:07:07,190 --> 01:07:08,624
and all got massacred.

1025
01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:11,861
It's better to just pay
100 coins every day.

1026
01:07:11,928 --> 01:07:13,362
Hold on!

1027
01:07:13,429 --> 01:07:14,931
What's with you people?

1028
01:07:15,632 --> 01:07:17,133
Why didn't you say that sooner?

1029
01:07:17,200 --> 01:07:18,468
We spent all our coins

1030
01:07:18,535 --> 01:07:20,837
to fight those
monsters and clear it.

1031
01:07:20,904 --> 01:07:23,673
Well, everyone who
tries to clear it has died.

1032
01:07:23,740 --> 01:07:24,941
So we assumed

1033
01:07:25,441 --> 01:07:27,243
that you would, too.

1034
01:07:28,111 --> 01:07:30,380
You saw how coins
come out when you die.

1035
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:33,349
The congressman
collected and shared them.

1036
01:07:33,883 --> 01:07:35,918
Who knew you'd come back alive?

1037
01:07:35,985 --> 01:07:37,921
Exactly.

1038
01:07:39,689 --> 01:07:41,891
Why'd this happen to the world?

1039
01:07:42,959 --> 01:07:46,863
Why are humans being punished?

1040
01:07:51,234 --> 01:07:55,338
Is this what Yu Jung-hyeok
was talking about?

1041
01:07:57,040 --> 01:07:58,241
Kim Dok-ja!

1042
01:07:59,175 --> 01:08:00,877
That means you
don't have any coins

1043
01:08:02,745 --> 01:08:05,281
to pay the survival fee!

1044
01:08:05,348 --> 01:08:08,050
3 minutes until
the survival fee payment.

1045
01:08:08,117 --> 01:08:11,854
Humans within this district,
prepare for payment.

1046
01:08:33,409 --> 01:08:34,920
1 minute until the
survival fee payment.

1047
01:08:34,944 --> 01:08:37,480
Everyone prepare for payment.

1048
01:08:38,047 --> 01:08:40,383
Hui-won, you need to
catch him now!

1049
01:08:54,831 --> 01:08:56,332
Why so surprised?

1050
01:08:57,233 --> 01:08:58,601
It's the barrier.

1051
01:08:58,668 --> 01:08:59,835
Didn't you know

1052
01:08:59,902 --> 01:09:01,422
you have to clear
the Scenario to pass?

1053
01:09:02,205 --> 01:09:04,774
Except for me,

1054
01:09:04,841 --> 01:09:06,641
you killed all the monsters
at Geumho Station.

1055
01:09:11,247 --> 01:09:12,448
Time's up.

1056
01:09:13,549 --> 01:09:14,684
Wait!

1057
01:09:14,751 --> 01:09:16,085
That reckless gallantry of yours

1058
01:09:16,152 --> 01:09:17,687
is always the problem.

1059
01:09:17,754 --> 01:09:20,089
That's why you will die.

1060
01:09:26,329 --> 01:09:27,430
Take cover!

1061
01:09:29,632 --> 01:09:32,501
All monsters have
been neutralized.

1062
01:09:32,568 --> 01:09:35,104
The daily survival
fee will be lifted.

1063
01:09:35,171 --> 01:09:38,174
You have cleared
the Main Scenario.

1064
01:09:40,877 --> 01:09:42,045
Who the hell are you?

1065
01:09:42,578 --> 01:09:45,381
Hey, what's with your attitude?

1066
01:09:45,448 --> 01:09:48,251
Looks like I saved you,
shouldn't you thank me?

1067
01:09:56,526 --> 01:09:57,760
Since I killed him,

1068
01:09:57,827 --> 01:09:59,095
you don't mind if I take these?

1069
01:10:04,801 --> 01:10:08,938
Don't be scared.
I can tell you're just beggars.

1070
01:10:09,005 --> 01:10:11,140
Still, thank you.

1071
01:10:12,642 --> 01:10:14,444
She looks scary. Let's go.

1072
01:10:15,478 --> 01:10:17,413
Where are you going?
Need to clear the Scenario.

1073
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:21,651
Ah, we just cleared the Scenario.

1074
01:10:21,718 --> 01:10:23,386
That's for your district.

1075
01:10:23,453 --> 01:10:24,787
But you just stepped over here.

1076
01:10:28,124 --> 01:10:29,325
What is this?

1077
01:10:29,392 --> 01:10:30,559
We're blocked again?

1078
01:10:30,626 --> 01:10:32,662
Just so you know,

1079
01:10:33,429 --> 01:10:34,897
the Scenario here isn't one

1080
01:10:34,964 --> 01:10:36,699
where you band together.

1081
01:10:37,233 --> 01:10:38,901
It's everyone on their own.

1082
01:10:40,970 --> 01:10:42,772
You just going to stand there?

1083
01:10:44,073 --> 01:10:45,575
You really should run.

1084
01:10:50,379 --> 01:10:51,614
Lee Ji-hye...

1085
01:10:52,281 --> 01:10:54,150
(Main Scenario #1:
Prove Your Worth)

1086
01:10:54,217 --> 01:10:56,486
In the novel, at
the first Scenario

1087
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:58,688
when everyone was panicking...

1088
01:11:00,757 --> 01:11:02,725
Ji-hye, what do we do?

1089
01:11:03,326 --> 01:11:04,326
Lee Ji-hye

1090
01:11:06,662 --> 01:11:08,264
survived on her own.

1091
01:11:09,866 --> 01:11:13,069
Day 4 of the Chungmuro
Station Scenario is starting.

1092
01:11:13,569 --> 01:11:15,104
10 minutes before monsters appear,

1093
01:11:15,171 --> 01:11:16,972
Green Zones will be created.

1094
01:11:17,039 --> 01:11:20,643
Take refuge in
a Green Zone to survive.

1095
01:11:20,710 --> 01:11:22,878
Current survivors: 104 people.

1096
01:11:22,945 --> 01:11:26,348
Number of Green
Zones for today: 52.

1097
01:11:26,415 --> 01:11:28,317
Find refuge in a Green Zone.

1098
01:11:35,124 --> 01:11:38,194
10 minutes left!

1099
01:11:38,261 --> 01:11:41,897
If you want to live,
750 coins per person!

1100
01:11:41,964 --> 01:11:44,667
It's safe in here!

1101
01:11:44,734 --> 01:11:46,803
10 minutes left!

1102
01:11:47,303 --> 01:11:48,838
There aren't many empty spaces!

1103
01:11:48,905 --> 01:11:51,240
Not many spaces left.
Closing in 10 minutes!

1104
01:11:52,108 --> 01:11:54,610
How much in cash for just me?

1105
01:11:56,112 --> 01:11:57,213
He said cash.

1106
01:11:58,147 --> 01:11:59,147
Look.

1107
01:12:00,082 --> 01:12:02,885
We don't take cash. Bring coins.

1108
01:12:02,952 --> 01:12:04,420
I don't have any coins,

1109
01:12:04,487 --> 01:12:06,098
but I'll give you as
much cash as you want.

1110
01:12:06,122 --> 01:12:07,289
- Mister.
- $20,000? $30,000?

1111
01:12:07,356 --> 01:12:10,092
Get lost, will you?
Can't you read?

1112
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:11,303
(1 night 1 person, 750 coins)

1113
01:12:11,327 --> 01:12:12,607
- Damn it.
- Can't you take this?

1114
01:12:13,996 --> 01:12:15,364
This is $100,000.

1115
01:12:15,965 --> 01:12:16,799
Please!

1116
01:12:16,866 --> 01:12:19,068
I said get lost! Forget it.

1117
01:12:19,135 --> 01:12:21,804
Hold on a sec!

1118
01:12:24,340 --> 01:12:26,308
Where'd you get $100,000 in cash?

1119
01:12:26,375 --> 01:12:28,711
I passed through
Myeongdong Station yesterday.

1120
01:12:28,778 --> 01:12:32,548
A guy there was
offering $100 per coin.

1121
01:12:32,615 --> 01:12:34,049
You never know when the world

1122
01:12:34,116 --> 01:12:35,718
might return to normal,

1123
01:12:35,785 --> 01:12:37,025
so I exchanged it just in case.

1124
01:12:38,454 --> 01:12:39,822
Did I do something wrong?

1125
01:12:40,857 --> 01:12:43,326
That's from my safe!

1126
01:12:43,993 --> 01:12:46,729
I'm rich in coins
thanks to fools like him

1127
01:12:46,796 --> 01:12:48,197
who still love paper.

1128
01:12:48,831 --> 01:12:52,702
My goodness, a young
guy like you, so clueless...

1129
01:12:53,536 --> 01:12:54,737
You'll die broke!

1130
01:12:56,739 --> 01:12:58,507
Intruder detected.

1131
01:13:08,651 --> 01:13:12,255
But why do those beggars
fight so hard to live?

1132
01:13:13,389 --> 01:13:15,625
The ones with no
money will all die anyway.

1133
01:13:21,097 --> 01:13:22,565
We haven't even started,

1134
01:13:22,632 --> 01:13:24,834
do we have to fight
like this every day here?

1135
01:13:26,903 --> 01:13:29,638
At midnight, monsters
will rush into the station.

1136
01:13:29,705 --> 01:13:32,007
You can live if you go
inside the green tiles.

1137
01:13:32,074 --> 01:13:35,044
We'll split up and look
for empty spots, but listen.

1138
01:13:35,578 --> 01:13:37,413
There may not be
enough spots for us five.

1139
01:13:39,749 --> 01:13:43,252
If you find one,
protect it at all costs.

1140
01:13:43,319 --> 01:13:45,621
Then at least one of us will live.

1141
01:13:46,389 --> 01:13:47,256
Got it?

1142
01:13:47,323 --> 01:13:48,734
(Main Scenario #3:
Green Zone (Day 4 of 5))

1143
01:13:48,758 --> 01:13:50,426
(Survive each night
in a Green Zone)

1144
01:13:52,595 --> 01:13:55,131
No spaces left in
Chungmuro Station.

1145
01:13:55,731 --> 01:13:59,201
To live, we must take
away someone else's space.

1146
01:14:00,403 --> 01:14:02,004
You're that prophet?

1147
01:14:04,840 --> 01:14:06,842
I heard it from Master.

1148
01:14:06,909 --> 01:14:08,444
Since you made it this far,

1149
01:14:08,511 --> 01:14:10,079
I guess it works for you.

1150
01:14:11,547 --> 01:14:13,316
Where is Yu Jung-hyeok?

1151
01:14:15,918 --> 01:14:17,753
He went out already.

1152
01:14:18,654 --> 01:14:21,324
This Scenario isn't at his level.

1153
01:14:23,359 --> 01:14:24,794
But why just stand there?

1154
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:26,795
If you're a prophet,

1155
01:14:26,829 --> 01:14:29,498
you'll know where the bonus
Green Zones appear.

1156
01:14:33,569 --> 01:14:36,372
What?
Can't bear to just save yourself?

1157
01:14:37,506 --> 01:14:38,941
Master said to tell you this.

1158
01:14:39,442 --> 01:14:41,777
He'll take your offer,
so leave the others

1159
01:14:41,844 --> 01:14:43,612
and survive on your own tonight.

1160
01:14:49,385 --> 01:14:52,088
Can't bear to just save yourself?

1161
01:14:52,655 --> 01:14:56,692
But I told you for sure
what happens if you win!

1162
01:14:57,827 --> 01:14:58,827
Hey,

1163
01:14:58,894 --> 01:14:59,996
let's go.

1164
01:15:03,799 --> 01:15:06,001
What did I say?

1165
01:15:06,068 --> 01:15:07,336
I told you they'd do it!

1166
01:15:07,937 --> 01:15:10,873
You give up.

1167
01:15:14,210 --> 01:15:17,546
At least one of us should live.

1168
01:15:19,648 --> 01:15:21,650
Get out of there!

1169
01:15:32,728 --> 01:15:34,997
6-1, 6-1...

1170
01:15:37,233 --> 01:15:41,003
5 tiles back from the 6-1 mark.

1171
01:15:43,906 --> 01:15:45,074
Dok-ja!

1172
01:15:48,044 --> 01:15:49,611
Dok-ja, we looked all over,

1173
01:15:49,678 --> 01:15:50,846
but there are no empty spots.

1174
01:15:51,781 --> 01:15:53,049
Gil-yeong, over here!

1175
01:15:56,118 --> 01:15:57,987
Is there anywhere
else we can look?

1176
01:15:59,955 --> 01:16:02,458
Everyone, listen up!

1177
01:16:04,427 --> 01:16:05,594
I'm Biryu the Dokkaebi,

1178
01:16:05,661 --> 01:16:07,563
in charge of this Scenario.

1179
01:16:07,630 --> 01:16:09,465
Less than a minute left,

1180
01:16:09,532 --> 01:16:11,567
but I don't see your desperation.

1181
01:16:12,234 --> 01:16:13,836
After a few days, are you tired?

1182
01:16:13,903 --> 01:16:16,639
Should I free
the monsters right now?

1183
01:16:17,339 --> 01:16:19,641
So I'll raise the tension a bit.

1184
01:16:19,708 --> 01:16:21,643
Those who don't have a spot yet,

1185
01:16:21,710 --> 01:16:24,213
this is your last chance.

1186
01:16:24,280 --> 01:16:25,981
One minute before starting,

1187
01:16:26,048 --> 01:16:27,649
some Green Zones will vanish,

1188
01:16:27,716 --> 01:16:29,718
and Bonus Green Zones will appear.

1189
01:16:41,097 --> 01:16:42,898
Dok-ja, we need to move...

1190
01:16:48,070 --> 01:16:51,640
Is this prophecy too?

1191
01:16:53,576 --> 01:16:55,444
In this Scenario,
it can't be helped.

1192
01:16:57,680 --> 01:16:59,215
At least take those spots.

1193
01:17:04,954 --> 01:17:06,222
If we push them out,

1194
01:17:06,922 --> 01:17:08,357
won't those people die?

1195
01:17:10,626 --> 01:17:11,961
If you want to live,

1196
01:17:12,962 --> 01:17:14,363
it can't be helped.

1197
01:17:15,564 --> 01:17:17,533
Can't we just fight like before?

1198
01:17:18,067 --> 01:17:19,334
How many monsters are there?

1199
01:17:19,401 --> 01:17:21,136
That's not how it works.

1200
01:17:21,203 --> 01:17:22,838
Without a spot, you'll die!

1201
01:17:22,905 --> 01:17:26,108
The teleport has formed.
Monsters are entering.

1202
01:17:46,195 --> 01:17:47,763
You need to take a spot!

1203
01:17:47,830 --> 01:17:48,997
You can do that!

1204
01:17:49,064 --> 01:17:50,633
Why don't you find one?

1205
01:17:59,942 --> 01:18:01,677
This is driving me crazy.

1206
01:18:05,581 --> 01:18:06,582
Wait up!

1207
01:18:08,751 --> 01:18:09,985
Go towards the teleport.

1208
01:18:10,553 --> 01:18:12,020
And over there!

1209
01:18:12,087 --> 01:18:13,789
Isn't it more dangerous there?

1210
01:18:14,290 --> 01:18:16,291
All Scenarios are designed

1211
01:18:16,358 --> 01:18:17,926
to entertain the Constellations.

1212
01:18:17,993 --> 01:18:19,361
As long as it's entertaining,

1213
01:18:19,428 --> 01:18:20,496
the rules can change.

1214
01:18:20,563 --> 01:18:21,830
Green Zones can appear

1215
01:18:21,897 --> 01:18:23,165
in the most dangerous places.

1216
01:18:24,633 --> 01:18:25,634
Hurry!

1217
01:18:27,903 --> 01:18:29,738
This doesn't seem right!

1218
01:18:50,025 --> 01:18:51,226
Huh?

1219
01:18:51,293 --> 01:18:52,828
There's one!

1220
01:18:52,895 --> 01:18:54,363
But mister...

1221
01:18:54,430 --> 01:18:55,564
Later, I'm busy!

1222
01:18:55,631 --> 01:18:57,799
You could've just stayed there,

1223
01:18:57,866 --> 01:18:59,401
why'd you come back?

1224
01:18:59,468 --> 01:19:00,669
There's this novel I know

1225
01:19:00,736 --> 01:19:02,838
where only the hero survived.

1226
01:19:02,905 --> 01:19:05,241
But that hero was a real jerk!

1227
01:19:11,447 --> 01:19:12,581
Yu Jung-hyeok?

1228
01:19:23,058 --> 01:19:24,726
Hey, Yu Jung-hyeok! Move over.

1229
01:19:24,793 --> 01:19:27,062
You don't need a Green Zone.

1230
01:19:28,631 --> 01:19:30,111
Want to fight
the Fire Dragon with me?

1231
01:19:31,066 --> 01:19:32,468
This is my condition.

1232
01:19:33,802 --> 01:19:35,170
Leave the kid, and come in.

1233
01:19:36,272 --> 01:19:37,773
Otherwise you'll die.

1234
01:19:41,910 --> 01:19:43,445
Hyeon-seong, grab this!

1235
01:19:58,627 --> 01:20:00,829
- Gil-yeong, stay here.
- What about you?

1236
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:26,088
If I eat this,

1237
01:20:26,155 --> 01:20:28,190
I'll be trapped in
the Illusory Prison.

1238
01:20:40,369 --> 01:20:41,670
I knew it.

1239
01:20:52,481 --> 01:20:54,783
The Illusory Prison is activated.

1240
01:21:08,330 --> 01:21:09,631
He hit him!

1241
01:21:13,168 --> 01:21:15,003
Time's running out, hurry!

1242
01:21:26,248 --> 01:21:27,950
Die, you prick!

1243
01:22:01,316 --> 01:22:02,584
Stop, stop!

1244
01:22:02,651 --> 01:22:04,119
Hey, I'm sorry.

1245
01:22:05,754 --> 01:22:06,822
It's my fault.

1246
01:22:07,689 --> 01:22:09,258
Wow Dok-ja, you're so cool!

1247
01:22:10,492 --> 01:22:12,327
Dear Author,
Yu Jung-hyeok once said,

1248
01:22:13,262 --> 01:22:14,863
"I can't help it"

1249
01:22:14,930 --> 01:22:17,232
"if others are
sacrificed so I can live."

1250
01:22:18,767 --> 01:22:20,235
Is that the novel's theme?

1251
01:22:21,203 --> 01:22:22,805
I can't accept that.

1252
01:22:23,906 --> 01:22:26,675
Sir, your novel is

1253
01:22:27,910 --> 01:22:29,044
the worst.

1254
01:22:38,987 --> 01:22:42,858
Yesterday, Min-seob died.

1255
01:22:43,992 --> 01:22:46,195
I'm trying to find
out the details,

1256
01:22:46,929 --> 01:22:48,764
but for now,

1257
01:22:48,831 --> 01:22:50,632
just try to focus on
today's mock exam.

1258
01:22:50,699 --> 01:22:52,835
(Science - Chemistry)

1259
01:23:10,652 --> 01:23:11,920
Author,

1260
01:23:12,821 --> 01:23:14,490
once I caused a friend to die

1261
01:23:15,157 --> 01:23:17,092
so that I could live.

1262
01:23:18,460 --> 01:23:22,664
In the novel, Yu Jung-hyeok
seemed to be telling me

1263
01:23:22,731 --> 01:23:24,500
it's not my fault.

1264
01:23:26,001 --> 01:23:27,402
That it couldn't be helped.

1265
01:23:31,039 --> 01:23:34,276
So I cheered for Yu Jung-hyeok.

1266
01:23:36,612 --> 01:23:39,081
Until I read the ending today.

1267
01:23:41,817 --> 01:23:43,819
For me, this ending is terrifying.

1268
01:23:48,123 --> 01:23:51,860
I'm scared it could
happen to me, too.

1269
01:23:56,698 --> 01:24:00,235
Sir, I wanted a different ending.

1270
01:24:01,370 --> 01:24:02,738
The ending I couldn't have,

1271
01:24:03,772 --> 01:24:06,374
when whatever sacrifice it took,

1272
01:24:06,441 --> 01:24:10,078
the hero survived to the
end with his companions.

1273
01:24:11,246 --> 01:24:13,215
Don't be ridiculous.

1274
01:24:13,282 --> 01:24:17,119
Yu Jung-hyeok is using
the Dream Conversation skill.

1275
01:24:18,153 --> 01:24:19,913
Then you should've
fought that bully and won.

1276
01:24:22,958 --> 01:24:25,327
I know what you want to do.

1277
01:24:25,928 --> 01:24:27,596
But helping each other and all?

1278
01:24:30,232 --> 01:24:32,301
Humans just aren't born that way.

1279
01:24:34,236 --> 01:24:36,538
I used to think like you once.

1280
01:24:37,940 --> 01:24:39,341
But after losing
so many colleagues

1281
01:24:39,408 --> 01:24:41,076
in hellish battles,

1282
01:24:42,911 --> 01:24:44,746
it becomes easier to fight alone.

1283
01:24:48,984 --> 01:24:50,419
Then

1284
01:24:52,254 --> 01:24:53,388
what do we do now?

1285
01:24:55,157 --> 01:24:57,192
Why do you think you
have to do something?

1286
01:24:59,361 --> 01:25:01,029
After all, you were nothing.

1287
01:25:04,132 --> 01:25:06,635
His wounds are too deep,
he's not recovering.

1288
01:25:12,040 --> 01:25:13,508
Dok-ja, are you okay?

1289
01:25:14,242 --> 01:25:16,712
I worried you'd be down
like that the whole day.

1290
01:25:19,214 --> 01:25:20,816
What happened to everyone?

1291
01:25:21,316 --> 01:25:22,551
What's wrong with Hyeon-seong?

1292
01:25:22,618 --> 01:25:26,087
Mr. Dok-ja, good to see you awake.

1293
01:25:26,154 --> 01:25:28,890
Hyeon-seong pushed
himself too hard.

1294
01:25:28,957 --> 01:25:31,159
Sang-ah also strained
herself trying to heal him.

1295
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:33,362
You're really okay?

1296
01:25:34,796 --> 01:25:36,465
Yes, but...

1297
01:25:38,066 --> 01:25:39,901
Did you fight
the monsters all night?

1298
01:25:41,236 --> 01:25:42,404
Because of me?

1299
01:25:44,439 --> 01:25:48,076
Time's up. We need to
go do the next Scenario.

1300
01:25:49,911 --> 01:25:53,048
My companions survived
outside of the Green Zones.

1301
01:25:53,749 --> 01:25:55,584
By pooling their strength.

1302
01:25:56,785 --> 01:26:00,589
Perhaps the way to
clear this Scenario...

1303
01:26:00,656 --> 01:26:02,858
Hyeon-seong and
Gil-yeong can't fight today.

1304
01:26:03,358 --> 01:26:04,960
Secure two Green Zones for them,

1305
01:26:05,027 --> 01:26:06,528
and we'll hold out on the outside.

1306
01:26:09,631 --> 01:26:14,169
But today, Yu Jung-hyeok dies.

1307
01:26:17,873 --> 01:26:19,717
On the last day of the
Chungmuro Station Scenario,

1308
01:26:19,741 --> 01:26:21,443
a Fire Dragon comes out.

1309
01:26:22,177 --> 01:26:24,279
Yu Jung-hyeok will
fight with it and die.

1310
01:26:24,913 --> 01:26:27,382
You said if he dies,
this world ends.

1311
01:26:27,449 --> 01:26:28,350
To be precise,

1312
01:26:28,417 --> 01:26:30,619
if the hero who can
save this world dies,

1313
01:26:31,420 --> 01:26:33,789
in minutes the world
will be destroyed.

1314
01:26:34,523 --> 01:26:36,057
To prevent that,

1315
01:26:36,124 --> 01:26:38,727
someone else needs
to fight the Fire Dragon.

1316
01:26:38,794 --> 01:26:40,195
If that's us,

1317
01:26:42,130 --> 01:26:44,499
it means one of us has to die?

1318
01:26:46,968 --> 01:26:48,336
I'll do it.

1319
01:26:49,037 --> 01:26:50,037
Besides,

1320
01:26:51,339 --> 01:26:52,339
if it weren't for Dok-ja

1321
01:26:52,374 --> 01:26:53,742
I would have died then anyway.

1322
01:26:56,111 --> 01:26:57,446
What should I do?

1323
01:27:00,649 --> 01:27:01,650
No.

1324
01:27:02,284 --> 01:27:04,004
There's something else
you must do, Hui-won.

1325
01:27:05,120 --> 01:27:06,120
I'll do it.

1326
01:27:06,154 --> 01:27:07,422
Wait.

1327
01:27:07,989 --> 01:27:10,625
That guy Yu Jung-hyeok
has a really high level,

1328
01:27:10,692 --> 01:27:12,961
on a totally different
scale than us.

1329
01:27:13,462 --> 01:27:16,765
If a person like that will die,
what about you?

1330
01:27:18,800 --> 01:27:20,635
Last night you all protected me.

1331
01:27:22,237 --> 01:27:23,472
Thank you.

1332
01:27:24,706 --> 01:27:29,544
Thanks to you, I now know
what I need to do today.

1333
01:27:30,045 --> 01:27:32,881
Current survivors: 57 people.

1334
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:35,717
Number of Green Zones for today...

1335
01:27:39,988 --> 01:27:41,756
We have an announcement.

1336
01:27:41,823 --> 01:27:43,291
Everyone, listen up!

1337
01:27:44,926 --> 01:27:46,428
As you know, this Scenario's rule

1338
01:27:46,495 --> 01:27:47,762
is everyone for themselves.

1339
01:27:47,829 --> 01:27:49,631
The concept is to
survive on your own.

1340
01:27:50,565 --> 01:27:51,399
But last night,

1341
01:27:51,466 --> 01:27:53,702
some of you survived
outside of the Green Zones.

1342
01:27:54,402 --> 01:27:56,671
Helping each other, no less.

1343
01:27:56,738 --> 01:28:00,108
Our dear Constellations
are very upset.

1344
01:28:00,175 --> 01:28:02,043
So today we'll be
raising the difficulty.

1345
01:28:02,110 --> 01:28:05,313
Current survivors: 57 people.

1346
01:28:05,380 --> 01:28:08,750
Number of Green
Zones for today: 1.

1347
01:28:08,817 --> 01:28:10,986
What? You can't do that!

1348
01:28:12,921 --> 01:28:14,289
Quiet down!

1349
01:28:16,091 --> 01:28:19,294
I'll decide myself who
gets that Green Zone.

1350
01:28:19,361 --> 01:28:21,062
Who should get it?

1351
01:28:21,129 --> 01:28:22,731
The kindest human?

1352
01:28:22,798 --> 01:28:25,166
The most unfortunate human?

1353
01:28:25,233 --> 01:28:27,736
Or the smartest human?

1354
01:28:29,070 --> 01:28:31,673
But I hear in your world,
being rich is best?

1355
01:28:31,740 --> 01:28:33,074
Then we'll do that.

1356
01:28:33,708 --> 01:28:35,343
A Green Zone has appeared.

1357
01:28:42,150 --> 01:28:44,953
If you want to live,
rise up and take this spot.

1358
01:28:45,587 --> 01:28:48,290
But even if you do,
it's only one spot.

1359
01:28:55,330 --> 01:28:56,464
Wait a minute.

1360
01:28:57,566 --> 01:28:59,568
Ji-hye, would you help me?

1361
01:29:00,402 --> 01:29:02,337
Why should I?
I'm going to take that space.

1362
01:29:04,272 --> 01:29:06,041
Join us instead, okay?

1363
01:29:09,811 --> 01:29:11,980
If you'd just stayed in that Zone,

1364
01:29:12,047 --> 01:29:13,215
we wouldn't be in this mess.

1365
01:29:15,417 --> 01:29:16,251
Everyone's going to die

1366
01:29:16,318 --> 01:29:17,953
because of your stupid courage.

1367
01:29:18,486 --> 01:29:20,955
That's why I need your help.

1368
01:29:21,022 --> 01:29:23,158
I've got an idea,
so if you'd only...

1369
01:29:23,225 --> 01:29:24,225
I said no!

1370
01:29:25,126 --> 01:29:26,961
You saw who got the Green Zone!

1371
01:29:27,028 --> 01:29:29,664
In this world, it's always
the strong who survive.

1372
01:29:30,665 --> 01:29:31,666
I think it's great.

1373
01:29:32,167 --> 01:29:33,768
It's simple and fair.

1374
01:29:34,302 --> 01:29:36,471
If you don't want
to die, just win.

1375
01:29:40,342 --> 01:29:41,443
It isn't enough

1376
01:29:42,711 --> 01:29:44,512
that you killed your
friend to survive?

1377
01:29:46,781 --> 01:29:48,149
Even as she died,

1378
01:29:49,050 --> 01:29:50,919
she didn't even
reach a finger to you.

1379
01:29:54,856 --> 01:29:56,424
I couldn't help it.

1380
01:29:59,628 --> 01:30:01,029
I couldn't help it.

1381
01:30:08,403 --> 01:30:10,005
I know you couldn't help it.

1382
01:30:11,706 --> 01:30:14,042
But you know what happened

1383
01:30:14,109 --> 01:30:15,389
when you tried to survive alone.

1384
01:30:33,595 --> 01:30:35,096
Bihyeong, you there?

1385
01:30:35,163 --> 01:30:36,765
Dok-ja, wow!

1386
01:30:37,299 --> 01:30:39,934
Just as you said,
our channel is going crazy!

1387
01:30:40,001 --> 01:30:41,603
The Constellations
love this story,

1388
01:30:41,670 --> 01:30:43,204
and donations are pouring in!

1389
01:30:43,271 --> 01:30:45,206
Let's cash in those donations now.

1390
01:30:45,840 --> 01:30:47,042
How much?

1391
01:30:48,009 --> 01:30:49,311
All of it.

1392
01:31:00,021 --> 01:31:01,923
When I tell you, shoot it all out.

1393
01:31:01,990 --> 01:31:04,292
Hold on, let me convert it.

1394
01:31:06,161 --> 01:31:07,162
Hey mister!

1395
01:31:08,763 --> 01:31:10,065
Gong Pil-du!

1396
01:31:13,401 --> 01:31:14,836
What does this bum want?

1397
01:31:19,474 --> 01:31:22,210
Hey, want to do some work for me?

1398
01:31:23,044 --> 01:31:23,845
What?

1399
01:31:23,912 --> 01:31:27,448
I'll hire you for the day.
How much will it cost?

1400
01:31:27,515 --> 01:31:29,550
I thought you were a bum,

1401
01:31:29,617 --> 01:31:30,785
turns out you're a madman.

1402
01:31:31,586 --> 01:31:33,154
Will 100,000 coins be enough?

1403
01:31:36,157 --> 01:31:37,258
100,000?

1404
01:31:37,926 --> 01:31:39,260
Sure, if you've got that much,

1405
01:31:39,327 --> 01:31:40,996
I'll do what you want for one day.

1406
01:31:41,863 --> 01:31:42,897
You've got the coins?

1407
01:31:43,531 --> 01:31:44,532
Of course I do.

1408
01:31:44,599 --> 01:31:46,000
Bihyeong, now!

1409
01:31:46,067 --> 01:31:48,970
Here it comes, 113,000 coins!

1410
01:31:49,037 --> 01:31:51,272
The Green Zone is
being re-generated.

1411
01:31:51,339 --> 01:31:52,407
My spot!

1412
01:32:11,626 --> 01:32:13,161
That crazy son of a gun!

1413
01:32:13,795 --> 01:32:14,795
Hey!

1414
01:32:14,829 --> 01:32:16,398
Hey, don't do that!

1415
01:32:17,999 --> 01:32:18,833
I'll shoot you!

1416
01:32:18,900 --> 01:32:20,502
Go ahead and shoot!

1417
01:32:25,106 --> 01:32:26,741
I know you couldn't help it.

1418
01:32:27,542 --> 01:32:29,944
But you know what happened

1419
01:32:30,445 --> 01:32:31,725
when you tried to survive alone.

1420
01:33:00,775 --> 01:33:02,177
Hey!

1421
01:33:03,211 --> 01:33:05,313
Damn you.

1422
01:33:05,380 --> 01:33:07,749
That madman really broke it.

1423
01:33:07,816 --> 01:33:09,217
Out of the way.

1424
01:33:09,284 --> 01:33:12,420
You jerk, what about my land?

1425
01:33:12,487 --> 01:33:13,721
What will you do now?

1426
01:33:13,788 --> 01:33:15,456
Monsters will enter in one minute.

1427
01:33:15,523 --> 01:33:17,492
The teleport is forming.

1428
01:33:19,794 --> 01:33:21,496
From the very start!

1429
01:33:22,030 --> 01:33:23,531
If those Green Zones didn't exist,

1430
01:33:24,032 --> 01:33:25,834
we all would have fought them.

1431
01:33:26,468 --> 01:33:28,503
We might all have survived.

1432
01:33:35,543 --> 01:33:38,279
100,000 coins have
been transferred.

1433
01:33:38,346 --> 01:33:39,080
What are you doing?

1434
01:33:39,147 --> 01:33:41,582
I bought you for today.
Keep your word!

1435
01:33:41,649 --> 01:33:42,717
What do you want?

1436
01:33:42,784 --> 01:33:44,652
I don't want a single
resident here to die!

1437
01:33:45,887 --> 01:33:47,422
I counted everyone!

1438
01:33:55,964 --> 01:33:56,965
Hey!

1439
01:33:57,465 --> 01:33:59,000
I won't charge you for today,

1440
01:33:59,067 --> 01:34:01,402
so those who want to fight, fight.

1441
01:34:01,469 --> 01:34:03,638
Those who can't,
come onto my land.

1442
01:34:03,705 --> 01:34:04,706
Hurry!

1443
01:34:13,781 --> 01:34:15,717
Guess I'll earn bucket
loads of coins today.

1444
01:34:16,985 --> 01:34:19,654
The Constellation Defense Master

1445
01:34:19,721 --> 01:34:21,489
gives emergency
defense to Gong Pil-du.

1446
01:34:28,630 --> 01:34:30,307
Gil-yeong and Hyeon-seong
can't join us today.

1447
01:34:30,331 --> 01:34:31,900
We need to fight for them, too.

1448
01:34:32,567 --> 01:34:34,802
Don't die, you two.

1449
01:34:48,416 --> 01:34:50,919
Die, you jerk!

1450
01:36:00,622 --> 01:36:01,656
Pil-du!

1451
01:36:02,190 --> 01:36:03,424
I'll stop that one.

1452
01:36:03,491 --> 01:36:04,635
You keep blocking the entrance!

1453
01:36:04,659 --> 01:36:05,660
Go quick!

1454
01:36:12,567 --> 01:36:13,567
Hey, Yu Jung-hyeok!

1455
01:36:17,572 --> 01:36:20,174
If you fight, you'll die.
I'll do it.

1456
01:36:26,781 --> 01:36:27,781
With that sword?

1457
01:36:29,951 --> 01:36:32,787
It was 4 days ago
you predicted I'd die?

1458
01:36:34,322 --> 01:36:35,623
Watch this.

1459
01:37:06,888 --> 01:37:09,390
There's a human in this area

1460
01:37:09,457 --> 01:37:11,259
with abnormal abilities.

1461
01:37:11,326 --> 01:37:13,527
With all the
Constellations' consent,

1462
01:37:13,594 --> 01:37:16,430
the difficulty
level will be raised.

1463
01:37:16,497 --> 01:37:17,665
What?

1464
01:37:54,902 --> 01:37:56,170
This wasn't in the novel.

1465
01:38:38,913 --> 01:38:40,681
Sang-ah! Pull him out quickly!

1466
01:38:40,748 --> 01:38:42,116
Then what about you?

1467
01:38:42,183 --> 01:38:44,118
This'll protect me from
the flames, at least.

1468
01:38:49,490 --> 01:38:50,490
Now!

1469
01:39:46,514 --> 01:39:47,782
Gil-yeong!

1470
01:39:51,018 --> 01:39:51,952
Gil-yeong.

1471
01:39:52,019 --> 01:39:53,488
What about Dok-ja?

1472
01:39:55,089 --> 01:39:56,090
Gil-yeong.

1473
01:40:04,899 --> 01:40:05,800
Gil-yeong, stop.

1474
01:40:05,867 --> 01:40:08,569
I'm okay. I can do it.

1475
01:40:18,112 --> 01:40:19,814
Gil-yeong, that's enough. Stop.

1476
01:40:20,515 --> 01:40:22,783
Stop it Gil-yeong, please!

1477
01:40:39,567 --> 01:40:42,570
Lee Hyeon-seong's
attribute is ready to blossom.

1478
01:41:14,201 --> 01:41:15,202
Sang-ah!

1479
01:41:35,856 --> 01:41:37,892
Lee Hyeon-seong has activated

1480
01:41:37,959 --> 01:41:39,119
Great Mountain Push, Level 4.

1481
01:41:44,732 --> 01:41:46,067
I'm coming, Hyeon-seong!

1482
01:41:52,873 --> 01:41:53,873
Ms. Hui-won!

1483
01:42:09,457 --> 01:42:12,193
I'll face the Fire Dragon somehow.

1484
01:42:12,693 --> 01:42:13,794
Listen closely.

1485
01:42:14,495 --> 01:42:16,196
In the dragon's chest

1486
01:42:16,263 --> 01:42:18,499
there's a round shell
with a core inside.

1487
01:42:18,566 --> 01:42:20,267
If we pierce the core,

1488
01:42:20,334 --> 01:42:21,802
we can defeat the Fire Dragon.

1489
01:42:21,869 --> 01:42:24,071
The problem is,

1490
01:42:24,138 --> 01:42:27,742
whoever breaks that
shell is sure to die.

1491
01:42:28,943 --> 01:42:31,045
If I break the shell,
I'm going to die.

1492
01:42:31,946 --> 01:42:33,847
Then Sang-ah should bind its arms,

1493
01:42:33,914 --> 01:42:35,616
and Hui-won must pierce the core.

1494
01:42:36,117 --> 01:42:37,851
If you defeat the Fire Dragon,

1495
01:42:37,918 --> 01:42:39,387
you'll receive a special ability.

1496
01:42:40,421 --> 01:42:41,455
Just once,

1497
01:42:42,123 --> 01:42:44,125
you can revive someone who died.

1498
01:42:45,960 --> 01:42:46,960
You get what I'm saying?

1499
01:42:48,596 --> 01:42:50,731
We need to trust each other.

1500
01:42:51,399 --> 01:42:53,668
This is the only way

1501
01:42:56,070 --> 01:42:57,505
that we can all live.

1502
01:43:48,389 --> 01:43:49,957
Dok-ja...

1503
01:43:54,328 --> 01:43:56,664
Hui-won! Now!

1504
01:44:04,271 --> 01:44:05,271
Hui-won!

1505
01:44:28,629 --> 01:44:31,298
The core's shell is re-forming.

1506
01:44:33,501 --> 01:44:34,835
What do we do now?

1507
01:44:51,585 --> 01:44:54,421
The only way to end this fight...

1508
01:45:51,445 --> 01:45:53,080
The core is pierced.

1509
01:45:53,147 --> 01:45:55,649
Now Yu Jung-hyeok will die.

1510
01:45:56,784 --> 01:45:58,419
Just like in the novel.

1511
01:46:03,457 --> 01:46:06,493
Kim Dok-ja, what now?

1512
01:46:24,044 --> 01:46:27,014
The hero has died.

1513
01:46:28,649 --> 01:46:32,152
I couldn't do anything.

1514
01:46:33,287 --> 01:46:36,323
Activating Yu Jung-hyeok's
Regression skill.

1515
01:46:40,628 --> 01:46:42,896
All matter in the present world

1516
01:46:42,963 --> 01:46:44,365
will cease to exist.

1517
01:47:19,300 --> 01:47:21,134
(The Ichthyosaur's Nucleus)

1518
01:47:21,201 --> 01:47:24,171
(has been exchanged
for Ether of Faith)

1519
01:47:24,238 --> 01:47:25,940
(Trade initiated by: Tls123)

1520
01:47:31,578 --> 01:47:33,747
(If you don't like the ending, )

1521
01:47:33,814 --> 01:47:35,749
(try writing your own)

1522
01:47:37,518 --> 01:47:39,186
(Then show me)

1523
01:47:39,253 --> 01:47:40,921
(the ending)

1524
01:47:40,988 --> 01:47:42,723
(that you want)

1525
01:47:47,628 --> 01:47:48,896
Hey Bihyeong!

1526
01:47:48,963 --> 01:47:50,831
Send me the item, quick!

1527
01:47:50,898 --> 01:47:53,734
Dok-ja, the world is
disintegrating now!

1528
01:47:53,801 --> 01:47:54,868
Just send it!

1529
01:48:06,814 --> 01:48:07,934
Broken Faith has transformed

1530
01:48:07,982 --> 01:48:09,717
into an Attribute Weapon.

1531
01:48:15,289 --> 01:48:18,258
There's still a chance.

1532
01:48:21,862 --> 01:48:23,063
Hyeon-seong!

1533
01:48:25,899 --> 01:48:26,967
Ms. Hui-won!

1534
01:48:35,009 --> 01:48:36,210
Sang-ah!

1535
01:49:23,190 --> 01:49:25,659
The Green Zone
Scenario has been cleared.

1536
01:49:26,760 --> 01:49:29,696
10,000 coins paid as a reward.

1537
01:49:30,397 --> 01:49:32,265
As an additional reward,

1538
01:49:32,332 --> 01:49:33,692
you receive
The King of No Killing.

1539
01:49:34,301 --> 01:49:36,770
Kim Dok-ja revived Yu Jung-hyeok

1540
01:49:36,837 --> 01:49:38,672
using the King of No Killing.

1541
01:50:01,528 --> 01:50:02,629
Yu Jung-hyeok.

1542
01:50:04,898 --> 01:50:06,066
Are you okay?

1543
01:50:08,068 --> 01:50:09,870
I didn't think you could do it.

1544
01:50:30,757 --> 01:50:31,925
Nice job!

1545
01:50:31,992 --> 01:50:33,360
Wow, we defeated that?

1546
01:50:44,538 --> 01:50:47,874
Dok-ja, what a sword!
Guess it wasn't defective.

1547
01:50:47,941 --> 01:50:50,310
Hyeon-seong, your skill
back there was so cool!

1548
01:50:50,377 --> 01:50:52,546
I should have acted sooner.

1549
01:50:53,313 --> 01:50:54,982
All of you did great.

1550
01:50:56,817 --> 01:50:58,752
I, who was nothing,

1551
01:50:59,753 --> 01:51:03,023
lived this story, and
met new companions.

1552
01:51:03,957 --> 01:51:05,526
Together with my companions,

1553
01:51:06,126 --> 01:51:09,496
we will write a new
ending to this story.

1554
01:51:10,497 --> 01:51:14,201
(Omniscient Reader: The Prophecy)

1555
01:51:14,902 --> 01:51:17,371
(Written and Directed
by Kim Byung-woo)

1556
01:51:17,871 --> 01:51:20,340
(Ahn Hyo Seop)

1557
01:51:20,841 --> 01:51:23,277
(Lee Minho)

1558
01:51:23,777 --> 01:51:26,246
(Chae Soobin)

1559
01:51:26,747 --> 01:51:29,216
(Shin Seungho)

1560
01:51:29,716 --> 01:51:32,152
(NANA)

1561
01:51:32,653 --> 01:51:35,122
(Kwon Eunseong)

1562
01:51:35,622 --> 01:51:38,091
(JISOO)

1563
01:52:10,090 --> 01:52:12,759
A new Scenario is starting.

1564
01:52:12,826 --> 01:52:15,195
All of the barriers are lifted.

1565
01:52:17,264 --> 01:52:18,765
Help!

1566
01:52:18,832 --> 01:52:19,832
Someone help!

1567
01:52:19,866 --> 01:52:21,168
Help!

1568
01:52:22,569 --> 01:52:23,837
Mr. Han?

1569
01:52:24,905 --> 01:52:26,006
Those idiots!

1570
01:52:26,073 --> 01:52:27,741
They killed everyone
at Geumho Station!

1571
01:52:28,242 --> 01:52:30,811
Children, the elderly, everyone!

1572
01:52:31,845 --> 01:52:33,080
Don't just sit here!

1573
01:52:34,014 --> 01:52:36,250
They're on their way here now!

1574
01:52:41,088 --> 01:52:42,256
So soon?

1575
01:52:52,165 --> 01:52:54,534
They're coming! They're coming!

1576
01:52:55,168 --> 01:52:57,504
(Current location:
Chungmuro Station)

